1
00:00:53,753 --> 00:00:56,239
???? [ Techno Beat ]

2
00:01:23,249 --> 00:01:25,752
???? [ Continues ]

3
00:01:59,752 --> 00:02:03,239
[ Man Narrating ]
THIS IS THE STORY
OF A MAN NAMED HUBERT,

4
00:02:03,740 --> 00:02:05,742
HUBERT FIORENTINI.

5
00:02:06,242 --> 00:02:08,244
FORTY-SEVEN YEARS OLD,

6
00:02:08,745 --> 00:02:10,747
TWO HUNDRED TWO POUNDS,

7
00:02:10,747 --> 00:02:13,750
SIX FOOT FOUR.

8
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:17,253
A MAN OF QUIET STRENGTH
WHO WOULDN'T HURT A FLY.

9
00:02:17,754 --> 00:02:21,241
THE THING IS,
THIS WOMAN IS NO FLY.

10
00:02:27,247 --> 00:02:29,249
THAT WAS OUT OF LINE.

11
00:02:29,249 --> 00:02:32,252
- GET TO THE STATION BEFORE
  PUNCHING THEIR LIGHTS OUT.
- WHAT? COME AGAIN?

12
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:39,242
YOU AND I HAVE TO TALK.
LET'S GO SOMEWHERE QUIET.

13
00:02:49,752 --> 00:02:51,738
[ Blowing Nose ]

14
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:58,244
I HAVE TO GO SEE JAWS.
LEAN ON THIS GUY
UNTIL HE BREAKS.

15
00:03:00,246 --> 00:03:03,750
MORNING, HUBERT.
HEY, HUBERT.

16
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:07,754
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]
YEAH?

17
00:03:07,754 --> 00:03:11,241
-MR. FIORENTINI,
 I FINALLY GOT YOU ON THE PHONE.
-HELLO, MR. VAN EYCK.

18
00:03:11,241 --> 00:03:14,244
I KNOW YOUR POLICE WORK
KEEPS YOU BUSY ALL DAY.

19
00:03:14,244 --> 00:03:17,747
THAT EXPLAINS WHY YOU HAVEN'T
RESPONDED TO ALL THE TELEPHONE
MESSAGES, I SUPPOSE?

20
00:03:18,248 --> 00:03:21,751
ACTUALLY, MR. VAN EYCK,
COME TO THE POINT BECAUSE
I'M WORKING ON A CASE.

21
00:03:21,751 --> 00:03:25,238
YOUR ACCOUNT IS OVERDRAWN
FOR THE THIRD TIME THIS MONTH.

22
00:03:25,238 --> 00:03:28,741
YOU HAVE UNTIL
THE CLOSE OF BUSINESS TODAY,
OR YOUR OVERDRAFT IS REVOKED.

23
00:03:28,741 --> 00:03:31,244
- IS THAT TO THE POINT?
- I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

24
00:03:31,244 --> 00:03:35,748
- NO!
- YOU WANTED TO
  SPEAK TO ME, SIR?

25
00:03:35,748 --> 00:03:38,751
HUBERT, YOU HAVE SOME PROBLEMS.
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU?

26
00:03:38,751 --> 00:03:43,239
NO, NO PROBLEMS.
JUST THE USUAL.
IT'S PRETTY CALM RIGHT NOW.

27
00:03:43,740 --> 00:03:46,242
YOU BEAT THE CRAP
OUT OF EVERYBODY YOU SEE,
IT'S A PROBLEM.

28
00:03:46,242 --> 00:03:50,246
IF YOU MEAN THAT YOUNG
FEMALE I'M QUESTIONING,
SHE'S ACTUALLY A MAN.

29
00:03:50,246 --> 00:03:53,249
WHAT DO YOU TAKE ME FOR?
NOT THE TRANSVESTITE,
THE OTHERS.

30
00:03:53,249 --> 00:03:55,251
THE OTHERS? WHAT OTHERS?

31
00:03:55,251 --> 00:03:58,254
HUBERT, HUBERT.
TRY TO PICTURE IT IN YOUR MIND.

32
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:06,246
- AH.
- AH.

33
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:09,249
SOMEONE INTERFERED IN MY DUTIES.
I ALMOST FORGOT ABOUT IT.

34
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:11,751
HUBERT, THAT'S NOT ALL.

35
00:04:17,740 --> 00:04:21,244
I ALMOST FORGOT.
A FIGHT BROKE OUT
AS I WAS LEAVING.

36
00:04:21,244 --> 00:04:24,247
GOOD. NOT THAT,
BUT I FEEL WE'RE GETTING CLOSE.

37
00:04:24,747 --> 00:04:28,251
- [ No Audible Dialogue ]
- SOME GUY BY THE STAIRS
  SAID SOMETHING TO US.

38
00:04:28,251 --> 00:04:31,254
THERE WAS TOO MUCH NOISE.
I COULDN'T MAKE OUT
WHAT HE SAID.

39
00:04:31,254 --> 00:04:33,740
- KNOW WHAT HE SAID?
- MY DAD'S THE CHIEF OF POLICE!

40
00:04:35,241 --> 00:04:37,744
- AH. IT SLIPPED MY MIND.
- AH.

41
00:04:37,744 --> 00:04:39,746
HE REMEMBERED.
THE OLD MAN'S OUT OF TOWN.

42
00:04:39,746 --> 00:04:42,749
- APOLOGIZE TO THE KID
  BEFORE HE GETS HERE.
- WHAT WOULD I SAY?

43
00:04:43,249 --> 00:04:46,753
WHATEVER YOU WANT. YOU THOUGHT
HE WAS A FELON YOU'VE BEEN
HUNTING. JUST FLATTER HIM.

44
00:04:47,253 --> 00:04:50,239
- I HAVE TO INTERVIEW
  THE TRANSVESTITE AND--
- HUBERT.

45
00:04:52,742 --> 00:04:55,745
- OKAY, WHERE DO I FIND HIM?
- WHERE YOU THINK
  YOU'LL FIND HIM?

46
00:04:58,247 --> 00:05:01,250
[ Knocking ]

47
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:04,253
HELLO THERE, IT'S ME.
YOU REMEMBER ME, RIGHT?

48
00:05:04,754 --> 00:05:07,740
- [ Groaning ]
- I RAN INTO YOU LAST NIGHT.

49
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:12,245
- [ Groaning ]
- NO, DON'T WORRY, I'M NOT HERE
  TO BUST YOU OR ANYTHING.

50
00:05:12,245 --> 00:05:14,247
I'M NOT HERE TO--

51
00:05:14,747 --> 00:05:17,250
NO, IN FACT I--
[ Groaning ]

52
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:19,252
I CAME TO APOLOGIZE.
[ Groaning Continues ]

53
00:05:19,752 --> 00:05:23,239
IT WAS SO DARK,
SO MUCH SMOKE. I DIDN'T KNOW
THE POLICE CHIEF WAS--

54
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:26,242
[ Muffled ]
WATER, WATER.

55
00:05:26,242 --> 00:05:29,245
ANYWAY, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE A BURGLAR.

56
00:05:29,245 --> 00:05:34,250
I MEAN, THIS HARDENED CRIMINAL
WEARS THE SAME BLACK SUIT,
RIGHT?

57
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:39,739
SO, WELL, I'M REALLY SORRY.
YEAH. I'LL BE GOING NOW. BYE.

58
00:05:49,749 --> 00:05:50,750
[ Cell Phone Rings ]
HELLO!

59
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:54,253
SOUNDS LIKE YOU'RE
IN A GOOD MOOD.
CAN'T YOU TALK?

60
00:05:54,253 --> 00:05:57,240
LOOK, SOFIA,
RIGHT NOW I'M REALLY
BUSY WITH A CASE.

61
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:59,742
SURE, NATURALLY.
BUT YOU'RE ALWAYS
BUSY WITH WORK.

62
00:05:59,742 --> 00:06:02,245
NOT ON SUNDAYS.
THAT'S TRUE, BUT THEN
YOU PLAY GOLF.

63
00:06:02,745 --> 00:06:06,249
- A MAN'S GOT TO RELAX SOMETIME.
- AND THAT'S PRECISELY
  WHAT I HAD IN MIND.

64
00:06:06,249 --> 00:06:08,751
AFTER GOLF,
I'LL PICK YOU UP, AND
YOU'LL TAKE ME OUT TO EAT.

65
00:06:08,751 --> 00:06:11,754
LOOK, SOFIA, LATELY
MY STOMACH'S BEEN UPSET.
I'VE LOST MY APPETITE.

66
00:06:12,238 --> 00:06:14,741
[ Hangs Up ]
"NO APPETITE"?

67
00:06:14,741 --> 00:06:17,243
WELL, THAT'S THE FIRST TIME
I'VE HEARD THAT ONE.

68
00:06:18,711 --> 00:06:21,214
WE TRIED EVERYTHING, HUBERT.
COULDN'T GET A THING.

69
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:23,716
THE DIRTIER WE GET,
THE MORE HE LIKES IT.

70
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:26,702
- MIND IF I TRY?
- SURE, GO AHEAD. BE OUR GUEST.

71
00:06:26,702 --> 00:06:29,705
IF YOU GOT TIME TO KILL.

72
00:06:37,196 --> 00:06:39,198
[ Gags ]
[ Tooth Rattles ]

73
00:06:43,703 --> 00:06:46,706
CIGARETTE.

74
00:06:55,698 --> 00:06:57,700
YOU REALLY HAVE A WAY
WITH WOMEN, LIEUTENANT.

75
00:06:57,700 --> 00:07:01,704
COMES NATURALLY,
I MEAN, A MAN AND A WOMAN
ARE MEANT TO GET ALONG, RIGHT?

76
00:07:02,205 --> 00:07:04,707
ANYWAY, WHERE ARE
YOUR GIRLFRIENDS? TELL ME.

77
00:07:04,707 --> 00:07:07,210
WOW.
AN IMPRESSIVE LOOKING PEN.

78
00:07:07,210 --> 00:07:11,197
IT WAS A GIFT.
I USE IT ONLY
ON SPECIAL OCCASIONS.

79
00:07:11,197 --> 00:07:13,699
NOW GO AHEAD.

80
00:07:13,699 --> 00:07:17,703
- WHO'D YOU GET IT FROM,
  A WOMAN?
- THE ONLY ONE FOR ME.

81
00:07:17,703 --> 00:07:20,206
SHE JUST DISAPPEARED AND...

82
00:07:21,207 --> 00:07:23,209
THIS IS ALL SHE LEFT BEHIND.

83
00:07:25,711 --> 00:07:29,198
OKAY, OLIVIER, GIVE ME
THE NAME OF THE BANK.
LET'S FINISH THIS.

84
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:38,708
BANQUE de l'Etoile.

85
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:41,711
EVERYBODY'S IN ON IT.

86
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:45,698
IT WAS THE LAST JOB.
OUR GRAND FINALE.
[ Grunts ]

87
00:07:45,698 --> 00:07:47,700
WHEN IS IT?

88
00:07:50,203 --> 00:07:52,705
- IT'S TODAY.
- WHAT TIME?

89
00:07:52,705 --> 00:07:56,209
IT SHOULD'VE STARTED 30
MINUTES AGO. YOU'LL BE LATE.

90
00:07:57,210 --> 00:07:59,712
PUT IT OUT ON THE WIRE!

91
00:08:03,199 --> 00:08:07,203
EVERYTHING UNDER CONTROL?
THEY'RE ALL INSIDE?
YOU SURE YOU CHECKED THE PLACE?

92
00:08:07,703 --> 00:08:10,206
[ Tires Squealing ]

93
00:08:10,206 --> 00:08:11,707
WATCH OUT!

94
00:08:14,210 --> 00:08:17,196
OH, FUCK, NOT HIM.
WE'RE COOL.
WE'RE IN GOOD SHAPE HERE.

95
00:08:17,196 --> 00:08:20,700
NOBODY'S COME OUT.
GOT ALL THE EXITS COVERED
AND A PHONE HOOK-UP.

96
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:23,703
SHOULD I TELL THEM SOMETHING?
SAY THEY GOT A VISITOR.

97
00:08:23,703 --> 00:08:26,706
SOMEONE'S COMING TO VISIT US?
BUT I'M NOT EXPECTING ANYONE!

98
00:08:31,711 --> 00:08:36,199
SO WHAT WE HAVE HERE, GIRLS?
NEED MONEY? WHY NOT USE
THE A.T.M. LIKE EVERYONE ELSE?

99
00:08:36,199 --> 00:08:40,703
OKAY, EVERYONE'S LEAVING.
I HAVE TO CLEAN UP HERE.
GO AHEAD.

100
00:08:43,706 --> 00:08:45,708
I GIVE THE ORDERS!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

101
00:08:45,708 --> 00:08:49,212
DON'T MOVE. ONE STEP
AND I'LL MAKE A HOLE
IN THIS MAN'S HEAD!

102
00:08:49,212 --> 00:08:52,698
SORRY, BUT I'M
THE ONLY ONE WHO CAN
PUT A HOLE IN SOMEONE'S HEAD.

103
00:08:52,698 --> 00:08:55,701
LOOK AT THIS.
THIS IS ALL THAT'S LEFT
OF YOUR GIRLFRIEND.

104
00:08:55,701 --> 00:09:00,206
NOW KISS YOUR PRETTY FACES
GOOD-BYE OR FORGET ALL THIS
AND SURRENDER.

105
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:03,209
IRENE, MY HEAD IS SPINNING.
HE'LL DO SOMETHING BAD TO US.

106
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:06,212
RELAX.
ALL THIS PRETTY DYNAMITE,
AND I HAVE A GUN IN MY HAND.

107
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:09,198
- HE WOULDN'T DARE TRY IT.
  HE'S BULLSHITTING.
- OH, YOU HAVE A GUN.

108
00:09:09,198 --> 00:09:12,702
FROM HERE IT LOOKED LIKE
ONE OF THOSE MACHINES
THEY USE FOR PIERCING.

109
00:09:12,702 --> 00:09:16,205
THAT'S GOOD. SO VERY FUNNY.
WHAT KIND OF EQUIPMENT YOU GOT?

110
00:09:19,709 --> 00:09:22,712
- [ Exhales ]
  LOOK AT THAT.
- THAT'S BIG ENOUGH FOR A HORSE.

111
00:09:24,196 --> 00:09:27,199
- GONNA HURT REALLY BAD.
- GIVE IT UP, GUY.

112
00:09:27,199 --> 00:09:30,202
THE BACKFIRE MIGHT JUST
BURN YOUR NAILS RIGHT OFF.

113
00:09:30,202 --> 00:09:35,207
IF YOUR COMEDY ACT'S DONE,
PUT YOUR B.B. GUN ON THE TILE,
AND PUSH IT GENTLY MY WAY.

114
00:09:35,207 --> 00:09:38,210
OKAY, BUT I WARNED YOU.

115
00:09:41,697 --> 00:09:44,700
[ Laughing ]

116
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:47,203
HEY, HOW DO I LOOK?
OKAY, GIRLS. GAME'S OVER.

117
00:09:47,703 --> 00:09:51,207
I'M GOING TO COUNT TO TEN.
DON'T WORRY, I'LL BE
NICE AND SLOW ABOUT IT.

118
00:09:51,207 --> 00:09:55,711
- WE'LL KEEP IT AT YOUR LEVEL.
- COME ON. WHAT YOU GONNA DO?
  I GOT YOUR PIECE RIGHT HERE.

119
00:09:55,711 --> 00:09:59,198
ONE, TWO--

120
00:09:59,198 --> 00:10:01,701
- STOP FUCKING AROUND.
  I'LL BLOW US ALL SKY HIGH!
- THREE--

121
00:10:01,701 --> 00:10:04,203
- [ Clicks ]
- AND TEN!

122
00:10:04,704 --> 00:10:06,706
[ Wailing ]

123
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:31,197
NOW WHY DID I EXPECT
TO BE LEFT ALONE TODAY?

124
00:10:36,702 --> 00:10:39,205
HUBERT, HUBERT.
IT'S SUNDAY, SIR.

125
00:10:39,205 --> 00:10:43,709
SURE, BUT EVERY DAY IS MONDAY
WHEN YOU'RE ON THE JOB.
I JUST SAW THE POLICE CHIEF.

126
00:10:43,709 --> 00:10:47,196
WHEN I TELL YOU TO APOLOGIZE,
WHY IS IT YOU RUB SALT
IN THE WOUND?

127
00:10:47,196 --> 00:10:49,198
ALL I DID WAS POUR
A GLASS OF WATER.

128
00:10:49,699 --> 00:10:52,201
LOOK, HUBERT, HE REQUIRES
AN OPERATION WHENEVER
YOU TWO CROSS PATHS.

129
00:10:52,201 --> 00:10:55,204
NO WONDER HIS OLD MAN
QUESTIONS YOUR METHODS.

130
00:10:55,204 --> 00:10:57,206
I JUST APOLOGIZED
AND BROUGHT FLOWERS.

131
00:10:57,206 --> 00:10:59,709
RIGHT, AND NOW HE'S GOT TWO
MONTHS IN SUSPENDED POSITION.

132
00:11:00,209 --> 00:11:03,713
AND THE POLICE CHIEF
SUGGESTED YOU--
YOU GET THAT TOO.

133
00:11:03,713 --> 00:11:05,698
TWO MONTHS' SUSPENSION.

134
00:11:16,208 --> 00:11:18,210
I SEE.

135
00:11:18,711 --> 00:11:22,198
HUBERT,
NO ONE CONTESTS YOUR RESULTS,
BUT YOUR METHODS, HUBERT.

136
00:11:25,701 --> 00:11:28,204
- WHAT'S WRONG WITH MY METHODS?
- THEY'RE COMPLETELY ILLEGAL.

137
00:11:31,207 --> 00:11:34,210
WE'RE NOT IN THE FAR WEST.
THERE ARE LAWS AND
A CODE APPLYING TO THE POLICE.

138
00:11:34,710 --> 00:11:36,712
AS A POLICE OFFICER,
YOU'RE REQUIRED TO RESPECT
THOSE TWO CODES.

139
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:39,699
RESPECTING THOSE CODES
LOST ME EIGHT GUYS
TWO YEARS AGO.

140
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:41,701
I GO VISIT OFTEN.
THEY APPRECIATE FLOWERS.

141
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:45,204
THEY'RE NO LONGER AMONG US.
TAKE A GOOD LOOK AT THE FACTS.

142
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:48,708
YOU'RE OUT OF STEP WITH REALITY.
NO FRIENDS, NO WIFE,
NO KIDS, NO ROOTS.

143
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:53,212
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO GET A LIFE,
HUBERT. GO START A FAMILY.

144
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:56,699
IT'LL MAKE YOU WANT
TO LIVE AGAIN, YOU'LL SEE.
COME ON. MAKE AN EFFORT.

145
00:11:57,199 --> 00:11:59,702
HUBERT.
YOU GOT A PROBLEM WITH WOMEN?

146
00:11:59,702 --> 00:12:03,205
- NO, OF COURSE NOT, BUT--
- SO HAVE YOU BEEN
  GOING WITH ANYBODY?

147
00:12:07,209 --> 00:12:09,211
I LOVED SOMEONE
BUT THAT WAS LONG AGO--

148
00:12:09,211 --> 00:12:12,698
EVERYONE'S HEARD THE STORY.
YOU MET A WOMAN
ON A JOB IN JAPAN.

149
00:12:13,199 --> 00:12:17,703
ONE DAY SHE JUST UP AND LEFT.
EVERYONE'S HEARD THE STORY.
BUT FIFTEEN YEARS HAVE GONE BY.

150
00:12:17,703 --> 00:12:19,705
- NINETEEN YEARS.
- OH, NINETEEN. FORGIVE ME.

151
00:12:20,206 --> 00:12:23,209
MOVE ON TO SOMETHING NEW.
YOU CAN'T SPEND YOUR WHOLE
LIFE CRYING ABOUT HER.

152
00:12:23,709 --> 00:12:26,712
DO ME A FAVOR,
USE THESE TWO MONTHS TO RELAX.

153
00:12:26,712 --> 00:12:29,698
- GO SHOPPING, HUBERT.
- I DON'T LIKE SHOPPING.

154
00:12:29,698 --> 00:12:33,202
OF COURSE YOU DO!
GO GET YOURSELF SOME NEW...
CLOTHING. HOW ABOUT THAT?

155
00:12:33,702 --> 00:12:36,705
A HANDSOME GUY LIKE YOU
IN A NEW SHIRT BY ARMANI.
BELIEVE ME,

156
00:12:36,705 --> 00:12:38,707
IT WON'T BE HARD
TO MEET SOMEONE.

157
00:12:38,707 --> 00:12:43,212
- YOU'RE SUSPENDING ME?
- NO. I'M SAVING YOU, HUBERT.

158
00:12:43,212 --> 00:12:46,699
GO BE A MAN A WHILE.
AND PROVE YOU'RE NOT
JUST A COP. ALL RIGHT?

159
00:12:51,704 --> 00:12:55,708
- DON'T YOU WANT TO COME IN?
- YEAH, YEAH.

160
00:12:55,708 --> 00:13:00,212
EXCUSE ME FOR STARING,
BUT THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
I'VE SEEN YOU WEARING BUTTONS.

161
00:13:00,212 --> 00:13:03,699
- ALL MY T-SHIRTS WERE DIRTY.
- OH, I FEEL MUCH BETTER.

162
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:10,706
WHAT'S WRONG?
NOTHING. I WAS GOING
TO TAKE YOUR COAT.

163
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:13,209
OH, I'M SORRY.

164
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:19,698
WHAT'S THAT LOVELY SMELL?
PORC AU CARAMEL!

165
00:13:20,199 --> 00:13:23,702
NO, I THINK IT'S YOU.

166
00:13:24,203 --> 00:13:27,706
YOU'RE WEARING COLOGNE?
IN THE BOTTOM OF A DRAWER
I FOUND AN OLD BOTTLE.

167
00:13:27,706 --> 00:13:31,210
THE BOTTLE THAT
I GAVE YOU TWO YEARS AGO?
THAT BOTTLE? REALLY?

168
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:33,212
REALLY. YOU GOT IT.

169
00:13:46,208 --> 00:13:51,197
APPETITE'S IMPROVED TODAY.
CAN'T LIVE ON BREAD ALONE.

170
00:13:51,197 --> 00:13:54,700
I'M OUT OF CHAMPAGNE,
BUT I HAVE SOME GOODSHOCHU.
THAT ALL RIGHT?

171
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:57,203
YEAH.

172
00:14:08,197 --> 00:14:10,699
- IS WORK GOING ALL RIGHT?
- [ Coughing ]

173
00:14:10,699 --> 00:14:14,203
- DID I SAY THE WRONG THING?
- I DON'T WORK ANY MORE, HUBERT.

174
00:14:14,703 --> 00:14:17,206
I STOPPED WHEN MY HUSBAND
PASSED AWAY. SEVEN YEARS AGO.

175
00:14:20,209 --> 00:14:22,211
HOW ABOUT A SPRING ROLL?

176
00:14:22,711 --> 00:14:24,196
A SPRING ROLL
WOULD BE JUST GREAT.

177
00:14:34,206 --> 00:14:36,208
THANKS.

178
00:14:39,211 --> 00:14:41,697
THAT WAS JUST PERFECT,
HUBERT. PERFECT.

179
00:14:41,697 --> 00:14:44,199
THANKS. IT'S, UH,
A SIMPLE DINNER, NO BIG DEAL.

180
00:14:44,199 --> 00:14:47,202
- WHICH YOU PROMISED ME
  TWO YEARS AGO.
- THAT LONG?

181
00:14:47,703 --> 00:14:49,705
- TIME SURE FLIES, HUH?
- YEAH.

182
00:14:49,705 --> 00:14:51,707
WHO TAUGHT YOU
JAPANESE CUISINE, YOUR EX?

183
00:14:51,707 --> 00:14:55,210
- RIGHT.
- I THOUGHT YOU ONLY SPENT
  EIGHT MONTHS WITH HER.

184
00:14:55,711 --> 00:14:59,198
WELL, BELIEVE ME,
YOU CAN LEARN AN AWFUL LOT
IN EIGHT MONTHS.

185
00:15:00,699 --> 00:15:03,702
GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT.

186
00:15:03,702 --> 00:15:05,704
- CALL ME A TAXI?
- RIGHT NOW?

187
00:15:05,704 --> 00:15:08,707
WHY DO YOU LOOK SO SURPRISED?

188
00:15:08,707 --> 00:15:11,210
I MEAN, WELL, IT'S UH--
 I MEAN--

189
00:15:11,210 --> 00:15:14,196
WE KNOW EACH OTHER
A BIT BETTER NOW, SO I--

190
00:15:14,196 --> 00:15:16,198
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
WANT TO STAY HERE TONIGHT.

191
00:15:16,699 --> 00:15:18,701
IN FACT THE NIGHT AIR
MIGHT CLEAR MY HEAD.

192
00:15:19,201 --> 00:15:22,705
I'LL WALK AND END
THE PERFECT EVENING
IN THE PERFECT WAY.

193
00:15:27,209 --> 00:15:30,212
SOFIA, I'M SORRY.
I DON'T GET IT.

194
00:15:30,212 --> 00:15:34,199
YOU'RE REALLY CUTE, HUBERT,
WHEN YOU'RE TRYING SO HARD.
BUT YOU DON'T TRUST WOMEN.

195
00:15:34,199 --> 00:15:38,704
HOW AM I TO TRUST WOMEN?
AS SOON AS I TURN AROUND,
THEY LEAVE OR BREAK MY HEART.

196
00:15:38,704 --> 00:15:40,706
I DON'T WANT TO DO EITHER.
YOU MUST UNDERSTAND,

197
00:15:41,206 --> 00:15:43,208
ALL I WANT IS TO SPEND
SOME TIME TOGETHER.

198
00:15:43,709 --> 00:15:45,711
THAT'S WHAT THEY MEAN BY "LOVE".

199
00:15:45,711 --> 00:15:48,697
NOT CRYING OVER SOMEONE
WHO'S BEEN GONE OVER 20 YEARS.
NINETEEN YEARS.

200
00:15:48,697 --> 00:15:50,699
NINETEEN YEARS, IF YOU PREFER.

201
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:55,204
BUT THAT JAPANESE WOMAN
WOULD STILL BE HERE TODAY
IF SHE REALLY LOVED YOU.

202
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:57,206
AND YOU'D HAVE HAD
BEAUTIFUL CHILDREN TOGETHER.

203
00:15:57,206 --> 00:16:01,210
BUT SHE'S GONE, HUBERT.
ALL THAT SHE LEFT WAS MEMORIES
AND A FEW RECIPES.

204
00:16:04,697 --> 00:16:07,199
THE SECOND YOUR HEART
IS FREE, CALL ME.

205
00:16:07,199 --> 00:16:11,203
I'M NOT VERY GOOD
AT JAPANESE CUISINE,
BUT I KNOW HOW TO PLEASE A MAN.

206
00:16:11,203 --> 00:16:14,707
OUR KIDS WOULD BE BEAUTIFUL.

207
00:16:14,707 --> 00:16:18,210
YOU'RE REALLY
LOOKING BURNED OUT.
YOU SHOULD TAKE A VACATION.

208
00:17:01,704 --> 00:17:05,207
I THINK IT'S TIME
WE SEPARATED. HOW ABOUT YOU?

209
00:17:21,707 --> 00:17:23,709
[ Phone Ringing ]

210
00:17:28,697 --> 00:17:31,200
- YEAH.
- MR. FIORENTINI, RIGHT?

211
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:33,202
LIEUTENANT,
PARIS POLICE DEPARTMENT?

212
00:17:33,202 --> 00:17:36,705
- YEAH? WHAT'S IT ABOUT?
- DO YOU KNOW A WOMAN
  NAMED MIKO KOBAYASHI?

213
00:17:38,707 --> 00:17:42,711
YEAH, I KNOW HER, YES.

214
00:17:42,711 --> 00:17:45,697
- YOU KNOW WHERE SHE IS?
- YES, AT THE MORGUE.

215
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:51,203
MRS. KOBAYASHI PASSED AWAY
YESTERDAY, IN TOKYO.

216
00:17:51,203 --> 00:17:53,205
I'M SORRY TO ANNOUNCE
SUCH SAD NEWS.

217
00:17:55,207 --> 00:17:57,709
I AM MR. HISHIBASHI.
I'M HER LAWYER.

218
00:17:57,709 --> 00:18:01,697
AND TOMORROW MORNING
I WILL BE EXECUTING
HER LAST WILL AND TESTAMENT.

219
00:18:01,697 --> 00:18:05,200
AS YOU ARE THE SOLE LEGATEE,
I WOULD LIKE YOU TO BE PRESENT.

220
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:08,704
SHE PUT ME IN HER TESTAMENT?
YES.
FROM BEGINNING TO THE END.

221
00:18:08,704 --> 00:18:12,708
BUT AS YOU LEFT JAPAN,
FINDING YOU WASN'T EASY.
TOMORROW AT THREE, OKAY?

222
00:18:12,708 --> 00:18:15,210
TOMORROW?
I'M-- I'M IN PARIS, I--

223
00:18:15,210 --> 00:18:19,198
THERE'S A FLIGHT
DEPARTING PARIS AT 6:00.
AND ANOTHER AT 8:30.

224
00:18:19,698 --> 00:18:22,201
OH.
I MADE
A RESERVATION ON BOTH.

225
00:18:22,201 --> 00:18:24,703
THERE'S A TICKET
PREPAID FOR YOU,
GOOD FOR EITHER FLIGHT.

226
00:18:24,703 --> 00:18:27,706
I CAN'T JUST GO.
I'LL HAVE TO TALK
WITH MY EMPLOYER.

227
00:18:27,706 --> 00:18:31,710
- I PUT A CALL IN TO YOUR C.O.
  MR. JAWS, RIGHT?
- RIGHT.

228
00:18:31,710 --> 00:18:36,198
HE SAID YOU COULD GO.
EVEN TOLD ME YOU COULD HAVE
AS MUCH TIME AS YOU WANT.

229
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:40,202
- I'LL THINK IT OVER, ALL RIGHT?
- THINK IT OVER, BUT HURRY,
  MR. FIORENTINI.

230
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:43,205
WHAT DOES IT MATTER NOW?
I'M IN NO RUSH.

231
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:47,209
WELL, YOU SEE, ACCORDING
TO THE WISHES, THE DECEASED
WILL BE CREMATED TOMORROW.

232
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:51,196
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
WANT TO SEE HER ONE LAST TIME.

233
00:18:51,196 --> 00:18:53,198
BE THERE.

234
00:18:53,198 --> 00:18:57,202
[ Jet Engines Whining ]

235
00:19:37,209 --> 00:19:39,211
DID YOU COME HERE
FOR VACATION OR BUSINESS?

236
00:19:39,211 --> 00:19:41,196
NEITHER ONE, SIR.

237
00:19:50,706 --> 00:19:54,209
EXCUSE ME. WHERE DID
YOU BOARD YOUR PLANE?
AT AN AIRPORT.

238
00:19:54,209 --> 00:19:57,696
YOU'RE VERY FUNNY,
BUT YOU HAVE TO USE HUMOR
WHEN IT'S APPROPRIATE.

239
00:19:57,696 --> 00:19:59,698
SORRY.
NOW, ANSWER THE QUESTION.

240
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,702
IF YOU LIFT YOUR EYES
TOWARD THE ARRIVAL BOARD,

241
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:06,205
YOU'LL SEE ONE FLIGHT
JUST GOT IN, FROM PARIS.

242
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:08,707
BUT IF YOU'D PREFER TO BE
LOOKING DOWN,

243
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:11,210
THEN THE TICKET ON MY BAG
HAS THE INITIALS "C.D.G.,"

244
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:13,212
THE ABBREVIATION
FOR CHARLES DE GAULLE AIRPORT.

245
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:19,701
YOU SEE I NOT ONLY
HAVE A SENSE OF HUMOR
BUT I'M ALSO FAIRLY OBSERVANT.

246
00:20:19,701 --> 00:20:22,704
ONE MOMENT.
I TOO AM OBSERVANT.
YOU ASKED FOR IT.

247
00:20:23,205 --> 00:20:25,207
OPEN YOUR BAG!

248
00:20:27,209 --> 00:20:30,712
JUST MAKE IT QUICK. I'M LATE.
YOU'RE LATE?
I'M SORRY FOR YOU.

249
00:20:39,087 --> 00:20:41,073
WHERE IS HE?
THERE. IN ROOM 138.

250
00:20:41,573 --> 00:20:44,076
HOPE HE'S STILL IN ONE PIECE.
OUR MEN AREN'T SAVAGES,
MAURICE.

251
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:47,079
IT'S JUST THE LAST TIME
I SAW HIM WAS YEARS AGO.

252
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:49,581
ALL BLOODY, I WON'T
BE ABLE TO PICK HIM OUT.

253
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:56,071
[ Speaking Japanese ]

254
00:20:56,071 --> 00:20:59,574
HANG ON. ONE SECOND.
I'M REALLY A NERVOUS WRECK.

255
00:20:59,574 --> 00:21:02,577
LIKE I CAUGHT THE BOUQUET.
SO HOW DO I LOOK?

256
00:21:04,579 --> 00:21:07,082
DO I LOOK PRESENTABLE?

257
00:21:07,082 --> 00:21:10,585
[ Man Shouting In Japanese ]

258
00:21:27,586 --> 00:21:32,074
- MOMO?
- HOW WONDERFUL!
  HUBERT, YOU RECOGNIZED ME!

259
00:21:32,074 --> 00:21:34,576
OH, HUBERT! HUBERT!

260
00:21:34,576 --> 00:21:38,580
HUBERT. OH, HUBERT. OH, HUBERT.
LET ME LOOK AT YOU.

261
00:21:38,580 --> 00:21:42,584
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL, MAN!
JUST ARRIVED AND ALREADY
IN DEEP SHIT.

262
00:21:42,584 --> 00:21:45,587
TRY TO BE
A LITTLE MORE DISCREET
UNTIL WE GET OUT OF HERE.

263
00:21:45,587 --> 00:21:48,073
YOU'RE RIGHT.
IT'S OKAY, HE'S ONE OF OURS.

264
00:21:48,073 --> 00:21:51,576
WHEN I WAS A ROOKIE,
I WORKED WITH THIS GUY.
HE WAS ALREADY A LIEUTENANT.

265
00:21:51,576 --> 00:21:55,080
WE WERE SPECIAL COMMANDOS
IN THE EIGHTIES, IN JAPAN
TO WATCH THE RUSSKIES.

266
00:21:55,080 --> 00:21:57,582
MAN, I CAN'T TELL YOU
THE TROUBLE WE MADE.

267
00:21:57,582 --> 00:22:02,087
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT. YOU CAN'T.
NOW TRY TO SPEND FIVE MINUTES
WITH YOUR MOUTH SHUT.

268
00:22:02,087 --> 00:22:06,074
I APOLOGIZE FOR THIS INCIDENT,
BUT YOUR EMPLOYEE INSULTED ME
AND I TAUGHT HIM A LESSON.

269
00:22:06,575 --> 00:22:09,578
I WAS A BIT OUT OF LINE.
SO PLEASE ACCEPT MY APOLOGIES.

270
00:22:09,578 --> 00:22:12,581
YOU DO HAVE A REPUTATION,
MR. FIORENTINI.

271
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:15,584
DO YOU HAVE A CASE IN TOKYO?
IS THAT WHY YOU'RE HERE?

272
00:22:15,584 --> 00:22:17,586
IT'S A VACATION.
DON'T WORRY,
I WON'T BE LONG.

273
00:22:17,586 --> 00:22:20,072
DON'T WORRY.
WITH MY FRIEND,
NOTHING TAKES TOO LONG.

274
00:22:20,072 --> 00:22:22,074
GOOD-BYE AND GOOD LUCK.
"GOOD-BYE AND GOOD LUCK."

275
00:22:22,074 --> 00:22:25,577
[ Laughing ]
"GOOD-BYE AND GOOD LUCK"

276
00:22:31,583 --> 00:22:33,585
FIFTEEN YEARS.

277
00:22:47,082 --> 00:22:49,584
- YOU'RE STILL
  DRIVING THE SAME CAR.
- I LOVE THIS BABY.

278
00:22:49,584 --> 00:22:53,071
YOU WOULDN'T
BELIEVE THE MILEAGE I GET.
SO WHAT ARE YOU UP TO?

279
00:22:53,572 --> 00:22:55,574
NOTHING, REALLY.
I'M ALL DONE WITH THE COMMANDOS.

280
00:22:55,574 --> 00:22:58,076
I'M JUST YOUR AVERAGE
NEIGHBORHOOD COP ON THE BEAT.

281
00:22:58,076 --> 00:23:00,078
I FINISH MY SHIFT
AND GO HOME.

282
00:23:00,078 --> 00:23:03,582
QUIT FUCKING ME AROUND.
TELL ME YOU TOOK UP KNITTING
WHILE YOU'RE AT IT.

283
00:23:03,582 --> 00:23:06,585
NOT KNITTING, BUT I PLAY GOLF
AND I'M ACTUALLY NOT BAD.

284
00:23:06,585 --> 00:23:09,571
GOD, HOW PITIFUL.
IT'S A GOOD THING YOU CAME BACK.

285
00:23:09,571 --> 00:23:14,076
WHAT DO WE BLOW UP? GOT A BOAT
WE COULD SINK? ARE WE GONNA
SABOTAGE A POWER PLANT?

286
00:23:14,076 --> 00:23:18,080
REMEMBER WHEN WE GOT
THE WRONG TARGET AND
TWO TONS OF AMMO BLEW?

287
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:20,582
OH, THAT WAS GREAT!
[ Laughing ]

288
00:23:20,582 --> 00:23:22,584
I'M HERE
ON A PERSONAL MATTER, MOMO.

289
00:23:24,086 --> 00:23:26,571
OH.

290
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:32,577
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
WITH THAT JAPANESE LADY?
WHAT WAS HER NAME AGAIN?

291
00:23:32,577 --> 00:23:36,081
- MIKO.
- MIKO. OH, RIGHT.

292
00:23:36,081 --> 00:23:39,084
SHE HAD YOU
ON A FREAKIN' LEASH.
[ Howls ]

293
00:23:39,084 --> 00:23:43,572
SHE JUST PASSED AWAY, MOMO.
I'M HERE FOR HER CREMATION.

294
00:23:43,572 --> 00:23:45,073
I HAD NO IDEA,
I'M REALLY SORRY.

295
00:23:45,073 --> 00:23:48,076
OKAY. HOW DID YOU KNOW
I WAS ARRIVING?

296
00:23:48,076 --> 00:23:51,079
WELL, I STILL WORK
WITH INTELLIGENCE.

297
00:23:51,079 --> 00:23:54,082
- COULD I DROP YOU OFF?
- HERE'S THE ADDRESS.

298
00:23:54,082 --> 00:23:58,587
SHINJUKU. AH, THE RED-LIGHT
DISTRICT. YOU GOT
THE PRETTIEST HOOKERS IN TOWN.

299
00:23:58,587 --> 00:24:01,573
OF COURSE, YOU'RE NOT
IN THE MOOD FOR THAT.

300
00:24:01,573 --> 00:24:05,076
???? [ Mid-Tempo Hip-Hop ]

301
00:24:34,573 --> 00:24:38,076
?? I JUST CAME TO SEE ????

302
00:24:40,078 --> 00:24:42,080
OVER THERE!

303
00:24:56,077 --> 00:24:59,080
HISHIBASHI-SAN?
HAI, DOZO.

304
00:25:06,571 --> 00:25:08,573
DOZO.

305
00:25:10,575 --> 00:25:13,078
OH, MR. FIORENTINI,
I ASSUME?
A GOOD ASSUMPTION.

306
00:25:13,078 --> 00:25:15,580
OH, BUT IT WASN'T DIFFICULT.
YOU'RE THE SPITTING IMAGE...

307
00:25:15,580 --> 00:25:17,582
OF THE PORTRAIT
MRS. KOBAYASHI DID OF YOU.

308
00:25:18,083 --> 00:25:20,085
BUT 20 YEARS OLDER OF COURSE.
NINETEEN YEARS.

309
00:25:20,085 --> 00:25:23,071
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S TRUE.
YOU'RE RIGHT TO BE PRECISE HERE.

310
00:25:23,071 --> 00:25:25,073
LET'S BEGIN RIGHT NOW.
HAVE A SEAT, PLEASE.

311
00:25:25,073 --> 00:25:28,076
- THANK YOU.
- MRS. KOBAYASHI NAMES YOU...

312
00:25:28,076 --> 00:25:30,078
AS HER SOLE LEGATEE.

313
00:25:30,078 --> 00:25:34,082
SHE LEFT YOU
ALL HER POSSESSIONS,
WHICH FOR PRACTICAL REASONS...

314
00:25:34,082 --> 00:25:37,586
HAVE BEEN PLACED
INSIDE THIS BOX.

315
00:25:37,586 --> 00:25:42,073
IF YOU WOULD BE SO KIND
AS TO SIGN THIS RECEIPT
AND THE ACCEPTANCE OF THE WILL.

316
00:25:53,084 --> 00:25:55,587
[ Sighs ]

317
00:26:19,578 --> 00:26:22,581
YOU WERE QUITE POETIC BACK THEN.

318
00:26:23,081 --> 00:26:25,584
BUT I PREFER THE PICTURE
OF YOUR UNIFORM PERSONALLY.

319
00:26:32,073 --> 00:26:35,577
[ Woman's Voice ]
WHERE IT ALL BEGAN,
WHERE IT ALL SHALL END.

320
00:26:38,079 --> 00:26:41,082
DID SHE EXPRESS ANY LAST WISHES
SHE WANTED ME TO CARRY OUT?

321
00:26:41,082 --> 00:26:43,585
ONE. ONLY ONE.

322
00:26:43,585 --> 00:26:47,072
THAT YOU BE THE GUARDIAN
OF HER DAUGHTER UNTIL
SHE COMES OF AGE.

323
00:26:49,074 --> 00:26:51,576
WHAT DID YOU SAY?
THAT'S RIGHT.
HER DAUGHTER.

324
00:26:51,576 --> 00:26:55,080
- HOW OLD IS SHE?
- NINETEEN YEARS OLD
  AND ABOUT ELEVEN MONTHS.

325
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:57,582
WELL, ARE YOU SAYING
HER MOTHER-- THAT HER MOTHER--

326
00:26:57,582 --> 00:27:00,585
ARE YOU SAYING THAT I--
THAT HER MOTHER--

327
00:27:00,585 --> 00:27:04,572
WELL, I MEAN--
BUT, WHAT? I MEAN-- WHAT-WHAT?

328
00:27:04,572 --> 00:27:07,075
- YOU MEAN WHAT'S HER NAME?
- RIGHT.

329
00:27:07,075 --> 00:27:10,078
HER NAME IS YUMI.
SHE MAKES QUITE AN IMPRESSION.
YOU'LL SEE.

330
00:27:10,578 --> 00:27:14,082
HANG ON THERE.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

331
00:27:14,082 --> 00:27:18,086
- I WAS GOING TO BRING HER IN.
- YOU MEAN THE DAUGHTER'S HERE?

332
00:27:18,086 --> 00:27:21,072
RIGHT BEHIND THE DOOR.
SHE GOT OUT OF PRISON
THIS MORNING.

333
00:27:21,072 --> 00:27:25,076
- GOT OUT OF PRISON?
- THE OFFENSE WAS MINOR.
  DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

334
00:27:25,076 --> 00:27:28,079
SHE HAD A SORT OF BREAKDOWN
WHEN SHE HEARD HER MOTHER DIED.

335
00:27:28,580 --> 00:27:31,082
DRANK TOO MUCH. AND THEN
SHE PUNCHED SOME POLICEMEN.

336
00:27:31,082 --> 00:27:34,085
- SOME POLICEMEN?
- YES, BUT I'LL LET HER
  TELL YOU ABOUT IT.

337
00:27:34,586 --> 00:27:38,573
WAIT A SECOND. WAIT.
WAIT. YOU BRING ME HERE
AND TELL ME...

338
00:27:39,074 --> 00:27:42,577
I HAVE A NINETEEN-YEAR-OLD
DAUGHTER I NEVER MET
WHO JUST GOT OUT OF PRISON.

339
00:27:42,577 --> 00:27:48,083
I ADAPT WELL TO NEW SITUATIONS,
BUT I'M GOING TO NEED TO THINK
ABOUT THIS FOR A SECOND, OKAY?

340
00:27:50,585 --> 00:27:53,071
HOW CAN YOU BE SURE
THAT I'M THE FATHER?

341
00:27:53,071 --> 00:27:56,574
BECAUSE IT SAYS SO RIGHT HERE
ON THE BIRTH CERTIFICATE.

342
00:27:56,574 --> 00:28:02,080
YOUR NAME IS WRITTEN
IN THE BOX NEXT TO "FATHER."
MRS. KOBAYASHI CONFIRMS IT.

343
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:05,083
ACCORDING TO HER TESTAMENT,
YOU ARE ONLY MAN IN HER LIFE.

344
00:28:05,083 --> 00:28:07,585
- WHY'D SHE LEAVE ME, THEN?
- THAT, SHE SAID NOTHING ABOUT.

345
00:28:12,574 --> 00:28:15,076
DID YOU SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT THIS TO YUMI?

346
00:28:15,076 --> 00:28:18,079
NO. I ASSUMED YOU
WANT THE PLEASURE
OF TELLING HER YOURSELF.

347
00:28:18,079 --> 00:28:21,082
OH, SURE, JUST IMAGINE.
SURE, I'VE BEEN AWAY
NINETEEN YEARS!

348
00:28:21,082 --> 00:28:24,085
- HELLO, I'M YOUR DAD!
- WELL, I IMAGINE
  SHE WILL BE VERY HAPPY.

349
00:28:24,085 --> 00:28:26,588
AFTER LOSING HER MOTHER,
SHE GETS HER FATHER BACK.

350
00:28:26,588 --> 00:28:30,575
BUT HOW CAN WE BE SO SURE?
HER MOTHER MIGHT'VE MET SOMEONE
JUST AFTER ME.

351
00:28:30,575 --> 00:28:32,577
HUH? A COUPLE OF MONTHS.
WHO COULD REMEMBER?

352
00:28:32,577 --> 00:28:36,081
I SUPPOSE YOU COULD
HAVE A D.N.A. TEST DONE.
SURELY YOU WOULD SETTLE IT.

353
00:28:36,081 --> 00:28:40,085
BUT FROM WHAT I'VE SEEN OF YOU,
I'M FAIRLY CERTAIN
YOU ARE HER FATHER.

354
00:28:45,573 --> 00:28:49,577
AND SHE'S RIGHT
BEHIND THE DOOR?
YES.

355
00:28:55,583 --> 00:28:59,087
LET'S KEEP THIS
TO OURSELVES.
NO MENTION OF FATHERS.

356
00:28:59,087 --> 00:29:01,072
ALL RIGHT.

357
00:29:03,575 --> 00:29:08,079
BECAUSE YOU COULD
TRAUMATIZE HER.
IT'S REALLY DANGEROUS.

358
00:29:12,083 --> 00:29:15,587
ACTUALLY, THEY'RE
FRAGILE AT THAT AGE.
I AGREE.

359
00:29:15,587 --> 00:29:19,073
EVEN IF THEY PRETEND
THEY'RE NOT.
VERY TRUE.

360
00:29:19,073 --> 00:29:21,075
SO ARE YOU GOING TO OPEN IT?

361
00:29:36,074 --> 00:29:38,576
[ Speaking Japanese ]

362
00:29:45,083 --> 00:29:47,585
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

363
00:29:47,585 --> 00:29:50,071
- SHE ASKED ME WHO YOU ARE.
- JUST TELL HER--

364
00:29:50,071 --> 00:29:52,574
JUST TELL HER I'M A GOOD
FRIEND OF HER MOTHER'S.

365
00:29:53,074 --> 00:29:56,077
[ Speaking Japanese ]

366
00:30:06,571 --> 00:30:10,074
- SO WHAT'S THE NAME
  OF THIS GOOFBALL?
- SAY MY NAME'S HUBERT.

367
00:30:10,074 --> 00:30:12,577
MR. FIORENTINI, SHE JUST
SPOKE TO YOU IN FRENCH.

368
00:30:14,078 --> 00:30:18,082
OH, RIGHT.
HELLO, MY NAME IS HUBERT.

369
00:30:19,584 --> 00:30:22,587
[ Scoffs ]

370
00:30:22,587 --> 00:30:26,074
IF YOU'RE NOT POLITE,
YOU GO BACK TO THE POLICE.
YOU NOT SCARE ME.

371
00:30:26,574 --> 00:30:29,077
WHO CARES ABOUT POLICE?
THEY ALL SUCK!

372
00:30:31,079 --> 00:30:33,581
- COULD I PLEASE HAVE
  SOMETHING TO DRINK?
- SAKE?

373
00:30:33,581 --> 00:30:36,584
YEAH, GREAT.

374
00:30:36,584 --> 00:30:39,087
[ Scoffs ]
[ Speaking Japanese ]

375
00:30:57,071 --> 00:30:59,073
THANKS. I FEEL BETTER.

376
00:31:08,583 --> 00:31:12,086
IF YOU'RE A FRIEND
OF MY MOTHER'S, WHY SHE
DIDN'T EVER TELL ME ABOUT YOU?

377
00:31:12,086 --> 00:31:15,073
YOU MUST KNOW YOUR MOTHER
HAD MANY FRIENDS FROM FRANCE.

378
00:31:15,073 --> 00:31:17,075
AND THOSE ARE FRIENDS
SHE MEETS THROUGH WORK.

379
00:31:17,075 --> 00:31:20,578
SO DID WE.
AT THE FRENCH CONSULATE.

380
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:25,083
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
-MR. FIORENTINI IS HERE...

381
00:31:25,083 --> 00:31:27,085
BECAUSE YOUR MOTHER
DESIGNATED HIM AS SOLE LEGATEE.

382
00:31:27,085 --> 00:31:31,573
HE WILL THUS TAKE CARE
OF YOU UNTIL YOU'RE OF AGE,
WHICH IS IN--

383
00:31:31,573 --> 00:31:34,576
TWO DAYS! THAT'S GREAT!
I DON'T HAVE TO BE
WITH HIM LONG!

384
00:31:34,576 --> 00:31:40,081
YUMI, BE CAREFUL HOW YOU SPEAK
TO YOUR-- YOUR GUARDIAN.

385
00:31:43,084 --> 00:31:46,588
THIS IS YOUR MOTHER'S
LAST REQUEST. I'M SURE
IF SHE CHOOSE MR. FIORENTINI,

386
00:31:47,071 --> 00:31:51,075
IF SHE TRUST HIM WITH SO MUCH,
SHE MUST HAVE THOUGHT
VERY HIGHLY OF HIM.

387
00:31:51,075 --> 00:31:53,077
EVEN IF SHE
NEVER TOLD YOU ABOUT HIM.

388
00:31:53,077 --> 00:31:56,581
NOW, IF YOUR MOTHER FELT
HE WAS SO WORTHY OF HER TRUST,

389
00:31:56,581 --> 00:31:59,584
HE MUST BE WORTHY
OF YOUR TRUST.

390
00:32:03,087 --> 00:32:05,573
WELL, FOR ABOUT TWO--TWO DAYS.

391
00:32:17,085 --> 00:32:19,087
COME ON.
LET'S GO SEE HER.

392
00:32:29,080 --> 00:32:31,582
WE CAN WALK THERE.
IT'S A FEW BLOCKS.

393
00:32:31,582 --> 00:32:33,584
WE COULD PROBABLY GET A TAXI.

394
00:32:33,584 --> 00:32:37,071
I'M VERY FRAGILE RIGHT NOW.
YOU HAVE TO BE
EXTREMELY INDULGENT.

395
00:32:37,071 --> 00:32:39,574
OH, OKAY. I WILL BE.

396
00:32:39,574 --> 00:32:41,576
BOY. THE OLD MAN
HAD ME FOOLED.

397
00:32:41,576 --> 00:32:43,578
COULD I
ASK YOU A QUESTION?
IT'S NOT UPSETTING.

398
00:32:43,578 --> 00:32:46,581
NO! FOR TWO DAYS,
I'M THE ONLY ONE
WHO ASKS QUESTIONS.

399
00:32:46,581 --> 00:32:49,083
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]
OH, OKAY.

400
00:32:50,585 --> 00:32:53,087
[ Speaking Japanese ]

401
00:32:57,575 --> 00:33:01,579
HEY, YOU STILL GOT IT, MAN.
TWENTY MINUTES ALONE AND
YOU GOT YOURSELF A PRINCESS.

402
00:33:01,579 --> 00:33:05,083
IDIOT! THAT'S MIKO'S DAUGHTER.
AND MY DAUGHTER, APPARENTLY.
GREAT BODY ANYWAY.

403
00:33:05,083 --> 00:33:09,087
WHAT?
NO, JUST I NEVER IMAGINED YOU
HAD CHILDREN WITH GREAT BODIES.

404
00:33:09,087 --> 00:33:13,574
WELL, IT'S NEWS TO ME TOO.
NOW FOLLOW AT A DISTANCE
AND SHUT YOUR TRAP.

405
00:33:14,075 --> 00:33:16,577
BOY, IS THIS
ABOUT TO GET MESSY.

406
00:33:21,582 --> 00:33:25,586
[ Speaking Japanese ]

407
00:33:32,076 --> 00:33:34,078
PSST.

408
00:33:36,581 --> 00:33:38,082
COME ON.

409
00:33:46,574 --> 00:33:49,577
HELLO, MIKO.
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

410
00:33:53,581 --> 00:33:57,585
YOUR MOTHER MANAGED
ALWAYS TO SMILE LIKE THAT,
NO MATTER WHAT.

411
00:34:01,072 --> 00:34:03,574
AND YOUR MOTHER
LEFT YOU HER SMILE.

412
00:34:09,580 --> 00:34:12,583
HAS IT BEEN VERY LONG
SINCE YOU'VE BEEN
WITH MY MOTHER?

413
00:34:12,583 --> 00:34:14,585
NINETEEN YEARS.

414
00:34:18,573 --> 00:34:21,576
WELL, THEN,
I'LL LEAVE YOU ALONE.
IT'S BEEN SO LONG.

415
00:34:21,576 --> 00:34:24,078
THE TWO OF YOU MUST HAVE
A LOTS OF STUFF TO SAY.

416
00:34:33,571 --> 00:34:36,074
WHY DID YOU KEEP IT
A SECRET? WHY?

417
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:45,083
YOU WANTED ME TO TAKE
CARE OF HER AND I WILL.

418
00:34:45,583 --> 00:34:47,585
BECAUSE SHE'S ALL
THAT REMAINS OF YOU.

419
00:34:56,077 --> 00:34:58,079
WAIT, WAIT.

420
00:35:15,079 --> 00:35:20,585
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- NOTHING, JUST A HABIT
  OF MY PROFESSION.

421
00:35:20,585 --> 00:35:24,071
- ARE YOU A DOCTOR?
- RIGHT, THAT'S RIGHT, A DOCTOR.

422
00:35:24,071 --> 00:35:26,574
- DO YOU KNOW HOW
  YOUR MOTHER DIED?
- YES. CANCER.

423
00:35:26,574 --> 00:35:29,577
YOU HAVE THE FILE
FROM THE HOSPITAL,
A DEATH CERTIFICATE?

424
00:35:29,577 --> 00:35:32,580
YES. THEY'RE AT MY HOUSE.
ARE YOU A SPECIALIST?

425
00:35:32,580 --> 00:35:36,083
UH, SURGERY.
PLASTIC SURGERY.

426
00:35:36,083 --> 00:35:41,072
AH, THAT'S GREAT!
WOULD YOU EXAMINE MY NOSE?
I WANT TO HAVE IT RE-DONE.

427
00:35:41,072 --> 00:35:43,574
LOOK AT THIS.
IT'S TOO BIG!

428
00:35:43,574 --> 00:35:47,078
IT'S NOT ATTRACTIVE
FOR A GIRL MY AGE TO
HAVE A NOSE LIKE THIS.

429
00:35:47,078 --> 00:35:49,580
- YOUR NOSE IS VERY PRETTY.
- IT'S HORRIBLE!

430
00:35:49,580 --> 00:35:53,584
- I MUST GET IT
  FROM MY BASTARD FATHER.
- HE'S A BASTARD?

431
00:35:53,584 --> 00:35:57,071
- HAVE YOU, UH--
  HAVE YOU YOU EVER MET?
- NO.

432
00:35:57,071 --> 00:36:00,575
IF HE SHOWED UP ONE DAY,
I WOULD SLIT HIS THROAT!

433
00:36:00,575 --> 00:36:03,077
WHAT'S HE EVER DONE
TO MERIT SUCH HATE?

434
00:36:03,077 --> 00:36:06,581
HE SEDUCED MY MOTHER AND
OBLIGED HER TO HAVE SEX.

435
00:36:06,581 --> 00:36:08,583
NO! NO.
YES.

436
00:36:08,583 --> 00:36:11,586
YES. BUT TOMORROW
I COME OF AGE,
AND I'M GOING TO GET...

437
00:36:12,086 --> 00:36:15,072
ALL THE YAKUZA
IN THIS COUNTRY AFTER HIM,
WHATEVER I DO!

438
00:36:15,072 --> 00:36:18,576
I THINK I BETTER
SIT DOWN FOR A SECOND.

439
00:36:23,581 --> 00:36:27,585
- YOU WANT SOME MORE SAKE?
- NO, I'M FINE. JUST THE CHAIR.

440
00:37:46,580 --> 00:37:49,083
YUMI, THIS IS
A FRIEND OF MINE, MOMO.

441
00:37:49,083 --> 00:37:51,585
HE'S BEEN LIVING
IN TOKYO FOR YEARS.

442
00:37:53,087 --> 00:37:55,573
WOW, WHAT A RESEMBLANCE--
MOMO.

443
00:37:55,573 --> 00:37:58,075
- UH, TO YOUR MOTHER.
- YOU KNEW MY MOTHER?

444
00:37:58,075 --> 00:38:01,579
NEVER MET HER, NO.
LET'S GET GOING.

445
00:38:06,584 --> 00:38:08,586
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]

446
00:38:10,571 --> 00:38:14,075
[ Speaking Japanese ]

447
00:38:14,075 --> 00:38:17,078
YOU TELL HER
YOU'RE A COP YET?
NO, SHE HATES COPS.

448
00:38:17,078 --> 00:38:19,080
IF I TELL HER, SHE'S GONE.

449
00:38:19,080 --> 00:38:22,583
I'M NOT LETTING HER GET AWAY
LIKE HER MOTHER DID.
SHE'S NOT A KID.

450
00:38:22,583 --> 00:38:25,086
TELL HER
AND SHE'LL ACCEPT IT
'CAUSE YOU'RE HER BLOOD.

451
00:38:25,586 --> 00:38:28,072
YOU'RE HER BLOOD.
BUT SHE DOESN'T EVEN
KNOW I'M HER DAD.

452
00:38:28,072 --> 00:38:30,574
IF SHE KNEW, SHE WOULD'VE
STABBED ME ALREADY.
I GUESS.

453
00:38:31,075 --> 00:38:33,077
[ Speaking Japanese ]

454
00:38:33,577 --> 00:38:35,579
HEY, DOES SHE KNOW
THAT MIKO'S HER MOTHER?

455
00:38:35,579 --> 00:38:38,082
SOMETIMES YOU'RE REALLY
VERY DUMB, YOU KNOW THAT?

456
00:38:38,082 --> 00:38:42,086
- WELL, OBVIOUSLY
  SHE KNOWS HER MOTHER.
- OKAY.

457
00:38:42,086 --> 00:38:46,574
THIS STORY GETS MORE COMPLICATED
BY THE MINUTE. I'M A LITTLE
MIXED UP, THAT'S ALL.

458
00:38:56,083 --> 00:38:58,085
[ Speaking Japanese ]
KONNICHIWA.

459
00:38:59,587 --> 00:39:02,073
[ Speaking Japanese ]

460
00:39:02,073 --> 00:39:06,577
THIS IS MY AUNT ATSUKO,
OLDER SISTER OF MY MOTHER.
MY GOD.

461
00:39:06,577 --> 00:39:08,579
KONNICHIWA.

462
00:39:08,579 --> 00:39:11,582
[ Speaking Japanese ]

463
00:39:11,582 --> 00:39:13,584
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

464
00:39:14,085 --> 00:39:18,072
SHE SAID SHE'S SEEN
YOUR UGLY FACE SOMEWHERE,
BUT SHE CAN'T REMEMBER WHERE.

465
00:39:18,072 --> 00:39:21,075
OH, GOOD.
UM, WELL, THAT'S TOO BAD.

466
00:39:21,075 --> 00:39:23,577
THE HOSPITAL RECORD.
OH, YEAH.
I'VE GOT IT OVER THERE.

467
00:39:23,577 --> 00:39:27,081
[ Speaking Japanese ]
MOMO, GO WAIT IN THE CAR.

468
00:39:27,081 --> 00:39:31,085
ARE YOU SURE?
COULD I TAKE A PISS?
NO.

469
00:39:31,585 --> 00:39:33,587
I DON'T THINK
 I CAN HOLD IT IN.

470
00:39:35,573 --> 00:39:38,576
WELL, ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

471
00:39:42,580 --> 00:39:46,584
- THIS IS A NICE ROOM.
- I WAS THINKING ABOUT
  CHANGING THE WALLPAPER.

472
00:39:47,084 --> 00:39:52,073
- WHAT DO YOU THINK?
- SURE. HOW ABOUT SOMETHING
  WITH ANIMALS? FAWNS, BEARS--

473
00:39:52,073 --> 00:39:55,576
SURE, AND PICTURES
OF WINNIE THE POOH.

474
00:39:55,576 --> 00:39:57,578
NO, NO, NO.
HERE'S WHAT I PICTURED.

475
00:39:57,578 --> 00:40:00,581
A NUCLEAR CLOUD
THAT'S EXPLODING IN THE AIR,

476
00:40:00,581 --> 00:40:06,587
WITH A LOTS OF SPACED-OUT
CHARACTERS ALL AROUND,
DANCING TO TECHNO.

477
00:40:06,587 --> 00:40:09,573
THAT WOULD PROBABLY BE
ALL RIGHT. WHAT'S YOUR
MOTHER'S BEDROOM LIKE?

478
00:40:09,573 --> 00:40:15,079
MOM CAME HERE ONLY ON WEEKENDS.
SHE HAD AN APARTMENT IN TOWN.

479
00:40:15,079 --> 00:40:18,582
- ALL RIGHT
  IF I PLAY SOME MUSIC?
- ALL RIGHT, GO AHEAD.

480
00:40:20,084 --> 00:40:22,086
???? [ Techno ]

481
00:40:28,075 --> 00:40:31,579
???? [ Stops ]
[ Chuckles ]

482
00:40:31,579 --> 00:40:34,081
WELL, MAYBE LATER,
OR SOME OTHER DAY.

483
00:40:34,081 --> 00:40:36,584
THE HOSPITAL RECORD.
YEAH.

484
00:40:39,086 --> 00:40:42,072
AH!

485
00:40:42,072 --> 00:40:44,074
OKAY, HERE IT IS.
THANKS.

486
00:40:45,576 --> 00:40:49,079
- WHAT DID SHE DO FOR A LIVING?
- SEARCH ME.

487
00:40:49,079 --> 00:40:51,081
MOM ALWAYS WAS
SORT OF MYSTERIOUS.

488
00:40:51,582 --> 00:40:55,085
THAT'S THE UNDERSTATEMENT
OF THE YEAR.

489
00:40:55,586 --> 00:41:00,074
- WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING
  FOR IN THERE?
- NOTHING! JUST ROUTINE.

490
00:41:03,077 --> 00:41:07,581
YOU'RE GONNA BE SPENDING
TWO WHOLE DAYS WITH ME, AND
IF YOU WANT THEM TO BE PLEASANT,

491
00:41:07,581 --> 00:41:12,586
YOU'VE GOT ABOUT TWO SECONDS TO
REALIZE I'M A GROWN-UP PERSON,
NOT A BLEEDING IDIOT!

492
00:41:12,586 --> 00:41:17,074
YOU TOOK SAMPLES OF CRYSTALS
THAT WAS UNDER HER NOSE,
AND THE DIRT UNDER HER NAILS.

493
00:41:17,074 --> 00:41:20,077
LOOK, THERE IS SOMETHING
STRANGE HERE, BUT INCONCLUSIVE.

494
00:41:20,077 --> 00:41:24,582
NOW AS A... MEDICAL DOCTOR,
YOU'VE GOT TO BE ABLE
TO SUPPLY EVIDENCE.

495
00:41:24,582 --> 00:41:27,084
YOU MEAN, LIKE THE POLICE?

496
00:41:27,084 --> 00:41:29,086
YEAH, LIKE THE POLICE.

497
00:41:29,086 --> 00:41:32,573
[ Sighs ]
I'M HAVING TESTS DONE.
WHEN I KNOW SOMETHING FOR SURE,

498
00:41:32,573 --> 00:41:35,576
YOU HAVE MY WORD
YOU'LL BE THE FIRST TO KNOW.

499
00:41:35,576 --> 00:41:38,078
DEAL?
YEAH, MAN.

500
00:41:40,581 --> 00:41:44,585
- YOU'RE PRETTY CLEVER, HUH?
- JUST A LITTLE.

501
00:41:44,585 --> 00:41:49,073
- WOULD YOU LIKE TO HELP ME
  TO TRACK DOWN MY FATHER?
- I'D BE GLAD TO.

502
00:41:49,073 --> 00:41:52,576
ARE YOU SURE YOU WANT
TO MEET HIM? SO SOON
AFTER LOSING YOUR MOTHER.

503
00:41:52,576 --> 00:41:56,080
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?
HE MUST BE FAR AWAY FROM HERE.

504
00:41:56,580 --> 00:42:00,584
TELL ME. WHO SAID THAT
HE FORCED HER TO HAVE SEX?

505
00:42:00,584 --> 00:42:03,587
MY MOTHER.
SHE'S GOT A LOT OF NERVE.
THA-THAT'S A SERIOUS CHARGE.

506
00:42:09,076 --> 00:42:14,582
YOU BELIEVE YOUR MOTHER WAS
THE KIND OF WOMAN WHO GETS
FORCED INTO THAT KIND OF THING?

507
00:42:14,582 --> 00:42:17,084
BUT WHY WOULD SHE
LIE TO ME THEN?

508
00:42:17,084 --> 00:42:21,572
PERHAPS TO PROTECT YOU,
OR TO PROTECT YOUR FATHER.

509
00:42:21,572 --> 00:42:25,075
WHAT REASON WOULD SHE HAVE
TO PROTECT A SCOUNDREL?

510
00:42:25,075 --> 00:42:27,578
MAYBE HE'S NOT
AS BAD AS ALL THAT.

511
00:42:39,573 --> 00:42:42,076
YEAH,
IT'S PRETTY UGLY WALLPAPER.
WE'LL GET IT CHANGED.

512
00:42:42,076 --> 00:42:44,078
RIGHT NOW!

513
00:42:49,583 --> 00:42:52,086
[ Speaking Japanese ]

514
00:42:52,086 --> 00:42:54,572
[ Giggling ]

515
00:42:57,074 --> 00:42:59,076
HI.

516
00:42:59,076 --> 00:43:01,579
TAXI!
GIVE ME YOUR PHONE NUMBER
AND HAVE THIS ANALYZED.

517
00:43:01,579 --> 00:43:05,082
WHAT IS IT?
IF I KNEW, I WOULDN'T
NEED IT ANALYZED.

518
00:43:05,082 --> 00:43:08,085
OKAY, YOU'LL
HAVE IT TOMORROW.
YOU'VE GOT AN HOUR.

519
00:43:08,085 --> 00:43:10,588
DAMN, SURE IS GOOD
TO HAVE HIM BACK.

520
00:43:10,588 --> 00:43:14,908
I WANT TO PUT SOME MONEY
IN YOUR ACCOUNT
FOR YOU AND YOUR AUNT.

521
00:43:14,908 --> 00:43:17,411
YOU'RE RICH?
NO, I HAVE
AN UNDERSTANDING BANKER.

522
00:43:17,411 --> 00:43:20,414
I'LL WIRE YOU MONEY EVERY WEEK.
YOU'LL USE IT AS YOU SEE FIT.

523
00:43:20,914 --> 00:43:23,417
THAT'S FUNNY.
THAT'S WHAT
MY MOTHER USED TO DO.

524
00:43:23,417 --> 00:43:27,404
THAT'S A COINCIDENCE.
YES, EVERY FRIDAY,
SHE'D WIRE ME $200.

525
00:43:27,404 --> 00:43:30,908
BUT IN TWO DAYS,
I'D SPEND IT.
WELL, JUDGING BY THE WILL,

526
00:43:30,908 --> 00:43:32,910
THERE CAN'T BE VERY MUCH
IN YOUR ACCOUNT.

527
00:43:34,912 --> 00:43:37,414
[ Speaking Japanese ]
WOULD YOU EXPLAIN
I WANT A BALANCE,

528
00:43:37,414 --> 00:43:39,416
AND THEN I'LL MAKE YOU
A WIRE TRANSFER.

529
00:43:39,416 --> 00:43:41,919
YEAH.
NO PROBLEM, SIR.
I HEARD YOU.

530
00:43:41,919 --> 00:43:44,905
OH. WELL, GREAT.

531
00:43:44,905 --> 00:43:48,909
AH.
WHAT'S THAT?

532
00:43:48,909 --> 00:43:50,911
ELECTRONIC SIGNATURE.

533
00:43:50,911 --> 00:43:55,416
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]

534
00:43:55,416 --> 00:43:57,918
[ Speaking Japanese ]

535
00:44:02,906 --> 00:44:04,908
HERE YOU ARE.

536
00:44:05,409 --> 00:44:07,911
THANKS.

537
00:44:14,418 --> 00:44:18,405
- AND UH--
  AND HOW MUCH TO THE YEN?
- OH, THAT'S A DOLLAR AMOUNT.

538
00:44:19,406 --> 00:44:22,409
OH.

539
00:44:25,412 --> 00:44:28,916
THERE MUST BE SOME MISTAKE.
WOULD YOU CHECK IT?

540
00:44:28,916 --> 00:44:34,405
OH, YES OF COURSE.
I UNDERSTAND YOUR SURPRISE.
THIS IS ONLY THE PRINCIPAL.

541
00:44:34,405 --> 00:44:38,409
THE INTEREST
IS ON A SEPARATE ACCOUNT.
SHOULD I GET IT FOR YOU?

542
00:44:39,910 --> 00:44:41,912
I SUPPOSE, YEAH.

543
00:44:52,406 --> 00:44:56,410
- THOSE ARE DOLLARS TOO?
- THOSE ARE DOLLARS.
  SHOULD I CALCULATE THE TOTAL?

544
00:44:56,410 --> 00:44:58,912
OH, NO, THANKS. SPARE ME.

545
00:44:58,912 --> 00:45:01,915
I GET THE PICTURE.
APPROXIMATELY.
[ Yumi Speaking Japanese ]

546
00:45:01,915 --> 00:45:04,918
BYE-BYE.
[ Speaking Japanese ]

547
00:45:05,919 --> 00:45:07,905
WELL? THERE ENOUGH?
LET'S SEE.

548
00:45:07,905 --> 00:45:11,909
YEAH, YEAH.
YOU--YOU--
YOU'RE DOING OKAY.

549
00:45:11,909 --> 00:45:13,911
AND THE WIRE TRANSFER, SIR?
IN WHAT AMOUNT?

550
00:45:13,911 --> 00:45:15,913
- HUH?
- WHAT AMOUNT?

551
00:45:19,416 --> 00:45:21,418
- TWO THOUSAND.
- DOLLARS?

552
00:45:21,418 --> 00:45:25,406
FRANCS.
RIGHT.
FRANCS?

553
00:45:25,406 --> 00:45:29,410
OH, THANK YOU, HUBERT!
I'LL ALWAYS REMEMBER
WHAT YOU DID FOR ME.

554
00:45:29,410 --> 00:45:31,912
NO, IT'S NOTH--
REALLY, IT'S NOTHING.
IT'S GREAT!

555
00:45:31,912 --> 00:45:35,416
- YOU'RE TREATING ME LIKE
  I'M YOUR OWN DAUGHTER!
- NO, I'M SURE YOUR FATHER,

556
00:45:35,416 --> 00:45:38,419
IF HE WAS IN MY SHOES,
WOULD'VE DONE THE SAME THING.

557
00:45:38,919 --> 00:45:44,408
RIGHT. BUT HE DISAPPEARED.
AND I'M REALLY A VERY HAPPY GIRL
TO HAVE YOU AROUND.

558
00:45:44,408 --> 00:45:48,412
SIGNATURE?
HUH?

559
00:45:48,412 --> 00:45:52,416
AND NOW WE GO SHOPPING!
WELL, BE REASONABLE.

560
00:45:52,416 --> 00:45:56,920
I NEVER SPEND ONE PENNY
MORE THAN WHAT I'VE GOT.
GOOD, JUST KEEP THAT UP.

561
00:46:29,419 --> 00:46:31,405
???? [ Humming ]

562
00:46:36,910 --> 00:46:38,912
TWO HUNDRED MILLION DOLLARS.

563
00:46:40,414 --> 00:46:43,417
- IT'S PRETTY, HUH?
- VERY PRETTY.

564
00:46:43,417 --> 00:46:45,919
[ Laughing ]

565
00:46:54,411 --> 00:46:57,915
COULD I BORROW
YOUR PHONE ONE SECOND?

566
00:47:00,918 --> 00:47:02,920
MOMO, GOT THE RESULTS YET?

567
00:47:02,920 --> 00:47:07,407
NOT ON THE FINGERNAIL SAMPLE.
BUT I JUST GOT THE RESULT
ON THE CRYSTALS.

568
00:47:07,407 --> 00:47:10,410
FERRO-MERCURIC POTASSIUM,
A.K.A.--
CYANIDE.

569
00:47:10,911 --> 00:47:13,914
IS THERE A TREATMENT FOR
LIVER CANCER USING CYANIDE?
I'LL BET THERE ISN'T.

570
00:47:13,914 --> 00:47:16,917
BUT HEY, YOU'RE THE DOCTOR.
AS A COP, WHAT'S YOUR OPINION?

571
00:47:16,917 --> 00:47:19,920
AROUND THE NOSE, CYANIDE.
THE HOSPITAL RECORD IS FICTION.

572
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:23,407
MARKS ON THE VICTIM'S HAND.
HER STRUGGLE WAS PROLONGED.
YOU CONCLUDE WHAT?

573
00:47:23,407 --> 00:47:27,911
THAT THE VICTIM WAS MURDERED.
AND THE MAN WHO MURDERED HER
WASN'T EXPECTING MR. FIORENTINI.

574
00:47:28,412 --> 00:47:30,414
- PUT IT ON THE WIRE.
  CODE SEVEN ONE.
- YES!

575
00:47:30,914 --> 00:47:34,418
- MEET ME IN ONE HOUR AT
  THE IMPERIAL. RESERVE A SUITE.
- HOW ABOUT EQUIPMENT?

576
00:47:34,418 --> 00:47:36,420
BRING ALL THE EQUIPMENT
YOU FIND.

577
00:47:36,420 --> 00:47:39,406
OH, MY GOD.
