FOR SOME REASON, SO SHE
LEFT ME CERTAIN KEYS.

652
00:54:25,912 --> 00:54:28,415
YEAH, KEYS.
AND $200 MILLION.

653
00:54:28,415 --> 00:54:31,918
JUST FORGET THE $200 MILLION.
SOMEBODY SAY IT WAS FOR YOU?

654
00:54:31,918 --> 00:54:35,405
YOU GOT SOME WAY
TO HAVE ACCESS
TO INFORMATION ON MIKO?

655
00:54:35,405 --> 00:54:38,908
THAT SHOULDN'T BE THAT
COMPLICATED. I KNOW A GUY
IN JAPANESE INTELLIGENCE.

656
00:54:38,908 --> 00:54:42,912
IF SOMETHING IN HER PAST
COULD EXPLAIN WHAT'S
GOING ON, I GOTTA HAVE IT.

657
00:54:43,913 --> 00:54:45,915
- I'M READY.
- READY FOR WHAT?

658
00:54:46,416 --> 00:54:48,918
I'M GOING OUT TONIGHT.

659
00:54:48,918 --> 00:54:51,905
BUT YOU CAN'T GO WEARING THAT.
IT'S, UH--
IT'S REALLY CHILLY OUT.

660
00:54:51,905 --> 00:54:55,408
PUT ON AN OVERCOAT
OR A JACKET.
A LONG RAINCOAT.

661
00:54:55,408 --> 00:54:59,913
I'M NOT PLAYING BRIDGE,
ALL RIGHT? I'M GOING DANCING!

662
00:54:59,913 --> 00:55:04,918
- ANYWAY, I'M ALWAYS TOO HOT.
  I TAKE AFTER MY MOTHER.
- YEAH, I REMEMBER HER MOTHER.

663
00:55:04,918 --> 00:55:08,405
YOU GO OUT BY YOURSELF
AT NIGHT? THAT COULD
BE DANGEROUS. RIGHT?

664
00:55:08,405 --> 00:55:10,907
- OH, YEAH, THERE'S FREAKS
  ALL OVER LOOKING FOR GIRLS.
- WHAT?

665
00:55:10,907 --> 00:55:14,411
NOT ALWAYS,
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

666
00:55:14,411 --> 00:55:18,415
WHEN YOU GOTTA GO,
YOU GOTTA GO. SO WHY
NOT HAVE A LITTLE FUN?

667
00:55:18,415 --> 00:55:21,418
COME ALONG AND CHAPERONE,
THEN NOTHING GONNA
HAPPEN TO ME.

668
00:55:21,418 --> 00:55:25,905
THAT WAY, YOU COULD
PRETEND THAT YOU'RE
BIG DADDY.

669
00:55:25,905 --> 00:55:29,909
I CAN SEE
YOU JUST LOVE THAT.

670
00:55:29,909 --> 00:55:31,911
BRING THE GRENADES.

671
00:55:33,913 --> 00:55:38,418
???? [ Hip-Hop ]

672
00:55:38,418 --> 00:55:40,420
[ People Chattering ]

673
00:55:51,414 --> 00:55:54,417
HEY, GUYS!
COME ON!

674
00:56:09,916 --> 00:56:12,419
DO DISCOS ALWAYS HAVE
VIDEO GAMES ALL OVER?

675
00:56:12,419 --> 00:56:15,405
COME ON.
[ Speaking Japanese ]

676
00:56:18,908 --> 00:56:22,412
[ Speaking Japanese ]

677
00:56:22,412 --> 00:56:24,914
UNCLE HUBERT AND UNCLE MORRIS.
MAURICE.

678
00:56:25,415 --> 00:56:27,417
HEY!

679
00:56:27,417 --> 00:56:29,919
THAT'S FUNNY.
HAI,IRENE.

680
00:56:29,919 --> 00:56:31,905
-IRENE.
- [ Speaking Japanese ]

681
00:56:32,405 --> 00:56:36,910
HAI,AADESHI.

682
00:56:36,910 --> 00:56:38,912
[ Speaking Japanese ]

683
00:56:40,914 --> 00:56:43,917
HAI,CHOLO.

684
00:56:46,920 --> 00:56:48,405
[ Speaking Japanese ]

685
00:56:48,405 --> 00:56:50,907
HAI,RIYUCHI.

686
00:56:58,415 --> 00:57:00,917
OKAY, COME ON EVERYBODY.

687
00:57:00,917 --> 00:57:02,419
- [ Speaking Japanese ]
- [ All Speaking Japanese ]

688
00:57:02,419 --> 00:57:04,904
ARE YOU READY?

689
00:57:04,904 --> 00:57:07,907
???? [ Dance ]
???? [ Singing In Japanese ]

690
00:57:39,906 --> 00:57:41,908
[ Speaking Japanese ]

691
00:57:41,908 --> 00:57:45,912
NO, THANKS, BUT I THINK
I'M A LITTLE OLD FOR THAT.
AND BESIDES, MY KNEE HURTS.

692
00:57:46,412 --> 00:57:48,414
HEY, WOULD YOU
DO THIS FOR ME, PLEASE?

693
00:57:51,417 --> 00:57:53,920
???? [ Continues ]

694
00:58:11,905 --> 00:58:13,406
CROSS YOUR LEGS TOO.

695
00:58:21,414 --> 00:58:23,917
-???? [ Ends ]
- [ Video Game ]
  KEEP PRACTICING. YOU CAN--

696
00:58:23,917 --> 00:58:27,420
YOU MADE ME PROUD OF YOU.
THAT WAS A GREAT TRY.

697
00:58:27,420 --> 00:58:31,908
- HEY, MOMO, IT'S YOUR TURN.
- OH, NO. I GOT PROBLEMS WITH
  MY KNEES, MY WHOLE BODY.

698
00:58:31,908 --> 00:58:34,410
MOMO!
MOMO! MOMO!

699
00:58:34,410 --> 00:58:38,915
MOMO! MOMO! MOMO!
OKAY, OKAY, SURE.
BUT ONLY ONCE.

700
00:58:38,915 --> 00:58:41,417
[ All Chanting ]
MOMO! MOMO! MOMO! YEA!

701
00:58:45,905 --> 00:58:48,908
???? [ Dance ]

702
00:59:10,413 --> 00:59:13,917
- HEY!
  [ Speaking Japanese ]
- WHAT DID HE SAY?

703
00:59:13,917 --> 00:59:18,905
IF YOU'D LIKE TO PLAY ANOTHER
ROUND, HE KNOWS A GAME THAT
WON'T BE HARD ON THE KNEES.

704
00:59:18,905 --> 00:59:20,907
- AND WHERE IS IT?
- OVER THERE.

705
00:59:20,907 --> 00:59:22,909
LET'S GO.

706
00:59:24,410 --> 00:59:27,413
HEY, WHAT IS IT?
I WAS WINNING.

707
00:59:27,413 --> 00:59:29,415
WHAT'S GOING ON?
I EXPLAIN LATER.

708
00:59:33,419 --> 00:59:35,405
[ Speaking Japanese ]

709
00:59:35,405 --> 00:59:37,407
YOU FIRST. YOU CAN
SHOW ME HOW TO PLAY.

710
00:59:37,907 --> 00:59:41,411
OK, MAN, YOU'RE UP.
OH. OKAY.

711
00:59:49,919 --> 00:59:52,905
[ All Speaking Japanese ]

712
01:00:22,919 --> 01:00:25,405
[ Screaming ]

713
01:00:37,417 --> 01:00:41,421
[ Speaking Japanese ]

714
01:00:47,910 --> 01:00:51,414
I THINK THE REMATCH
WILL HAVE TO WAIT.
OKAY WITH YOU?

715
01:00:51,414 --> 01:00:54,917
- ANY OTHER WAY OUT?
- OVER THERE.

716
01:01:00,406 --> 01:01:02,909
[ Chuckles ]
I'M SURE GLAD HE'S BACK.

717
01:01:06,412 --> 01:01:08,414
[ Vomits, Coughing ]

718
01:01:10,416 --> 01:01:13,419
I'M SORRY. I DIDN'T MEAN
TO RUIN YOUR EVENING.

719
01:01:17,907 --> 01:01:20,910
- WHO ARE YOU?
- UH, UH, I'M NOT A DOCTOR.

720
01:01:20,910 --> 01:01:23,913
YEAH, THAT'S PRETTY CLEAR.
YOU MADE THAT OBVIOUS
JUST NOW.

721
01:01:26,416 --> 01:01:29,419
TELL ME WHO YOU ARE,
TO KILL PEOPLE LIKE THAT.

722
01:01:29,419 --> 01:01:31,904
TELL ME WHY
YOU KILLED THEM.

723
01:01:31,904 --> 01:01:35,408
TELL ME WHO THOSE MEN WERE
AND WHY THEY HAD GUNS.

724
01:01:35,908 --> 01:01:37,910
[ Speaking Japanese ]

725
01:01:49,906 --> 01:01:53,910
- DID YOU CATCH ANY OF THAT?
- NO, IT DOESN'T MATTER.
  IT'S GOING TO BE ALL RIGHT.

726
01:01:53,910 --> 01:01:56,913
[ Sniffling ]
IF YOU'LL LET ME,
I'LL EXPLAIN.

727
01:01:56,913 --> 01:02:00,917
HERE, DRY YOUR TEARS.
[ Coughing ]

728
01:02:00,917 --> 01:02:04,420
AH, THAT REMINDS ME
OF A GUY I KNOW.

729
01:02:04,420 --> 01:02:07,907
GO GET THE STUFF ON MIKO
INSTEAD OF ACTING SILLY.
AND THE LAB REPORT...

730
01:02:07,907 --> 01:02:09,909
ON THE DIRT
UNDER HER FINGERNAILS.

731
01:02:09,909 --> 01:02:12,912
I'LL MEET YOU AT THE HOTEL
IN AN HOUR.
I SPEND MY LIFE IN MY CAR.

732
01:02:12,912 --> 01:02:15,415
MOMO--
OKAY.

733
01:02:38,421 --> 01:02:42,408
[ Sighs ]
YOUR MOTHER ASKED ME
TO COME HERE.

734
01:02:42,408 --> 01:02:47,413
SHE TRUSTED NO ONE.
BUT EVEN AFTER ALL THESE YEARS,
I THINK SHE TRUSTED ME.

735
01:02:47,914 --> 01:02:51,918
YOUR MOTHER WANTED ME HERE
SO I'D KNOW SOMETHING, A SECRET.

736
01:02:51,918 --> 01:02:55,905
BUT SHE WAS KILLED BEFORE
SHE HAD A CHANCE TO EXPLAIN.

737
01:02:55,905 --> 01:03:01,410
NOW SOME MEN IN DARK SUNGLASSES
HAVE BEEN FOLLOWING US ALL OVER.
FOR SOME REASON, THEY WANT YOU.

738
01:03:01,410 --> 01:03:05,414
ME? WHY? I MEAN,
WHAT HAVE I DONE?
WHY WOULD SOMEBODY HARM ME?

739
01:03:07,416 --> 01:03:10,419
THAT'S WHAT
I'VE BEEN WONDERING.

740
01:03:10,419 --> 01:03:13,406
REMEMBER YOU SAID
YOUR MOTHER KEPT
AN APARTMENT IN TOWN?

741
01:03:14,907 --> 01:03:18,911
SHE BROUGHT ME THERE
ONE FRIDAY, TWO YEARS AGO.

742
01:03:19,412 --> 01:03:23,416
SHE FORGOT SOMETHING
THAT WAS IMPORTANT, SHE SAID.

743
01:03:23,416 --> 01:03:26,919
SO I CAME ALONG.
BUT I STAYED
OUTSIDE THE DOOR.

744
01:03:26,919 --> 01:03:31,407
SHE WENT IN,
WOULDN'T LET ME INSIDE.

745
01:03:31,407 --> 01:03:36,913
I ARGUED. I SAID I JUST
WANTED TO GO IN FOR A WHILE
TO SEE WHERE SHE LIVED.

746
01:03:36,913 --> 01:03:38,915
SHE SLAPPED ME ACROSS THE CHEEK.

747
01:03:47,406 --> 01:03:50,409
IT WAS ONLY ONCE.
THE ONLY TIME SHE HIT ME.

748
01:03:57,917 --> 01:04:00,419
DO YOU STILL
KNOW THE ADDRESS?

749
01:04:26,379 --> 01:04:29,365
WAS YOUR MOTHER
ALWAYS SO ZEN?

750
01:04:29,866 --> 01:04:32,368
SHE WAS PRETTY ORGANIZED.
BUT I MEAN, COME ON!

751
01:04:32,368 --> 01:04:34,370
THEN SOMEONE'S
BEEN HERE ALREADY.

752
01:04:36,873 --> 01:04:39,375
BUT REMOVING FURNITURE?
IT'S TOO MUCH TROUBLE.

753
01:04:39,375 --> 01:04:42,879
THEY WERE AFTER SOMETHING.

754
01:04:42,879 --> 01:04:45,865
BUT THEY DIDN'T
KNOW YOUR MOTHER.

755
01:04:45,865 --> 01:04:50,369
YOUR MOTHER
WOULDN'T HIDE SOMETHING
IN ANOTHER MOVEABLE OBJECT.

756
01:04:50,369 --> 01:04:52,872
[ Hollow Knock ]

757
01:04:52,872 --> 01:04:55,374
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
- YOU'LL SEE IN A MINUTE.

758
01:05:02,365 --> 01:05:06,369
OKAY, BUT I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
EXPLAIN WHY MY MOTHER
HIDE THIS IN THE WALL.

759
01:05:06,369 --> 01:05:08,871
'CAUSE THAT'S
PRECISELY WHAT I'D DO.

760
01:05:09,372 --> 01:05:11,874
TELL ME. WHAT IS THIS?

761
01:05:16,379 --> 01:05:18,364
NUMBERS AND NAMES.

762
01:05:18,364 --> 01:05:21,367
NOW I'M STARTING
TO HAVE A COUPLE OF IDEAS.

763
01:05:21,367 --> 01:05:23,869
YEAH, WELL, I'M CONFUSED.

764
01:05:23,869 --> 01:05:26,372
YOU MURDER PEOPLE
AND MAKE HOLES IN THE WALLS,

765
01:05:26,372 --> 01:05:29,375
I JUST LOST MY MOTHER
AND I DON'T KNOW ANY MORE.

766
01:05:29,375 --> 01:05:32,878
YUMI, LOOK, I'M ASKING
FOR YOUR TRUST.

767
01:05:33,379 --> 01:05:36,365
THIS WHOLE NIGHTMARE
WILL SOON END.

768
01:05:36,365 --> 01:05:38,367
ALL RIGHT?
OKAY, LET'S GO.

769
01:05:43,873 --> 01:05:47,376
OH, WELL, AT LEAST
THE FURNITURE
DIDN'T DISAPPEAR.

770
01:05:54,867 --> 01:05:56,869
WHAT ARE THEY AFTER?

771
01:05:56,869 --> 01:05:59,872
NOTHING, IN MY OPINION.
LOOKS TO ME LIKE
SOME KIND OF INTIMIDATION.

772
01:06:01,374 --> 01:06:04,377
THEY SHOULD BE GETTING
IN TOUCH WITH US SOON.

773
01:06:04,377 --> 01:06:08,864
THEN WHAT DO WE DO?
SHOULD WE RUN?
NO. WE SIT DOWN AND WAIT.

774
01:06:10,866 --> 01:06:12,868
AH, WELL, THEY DIDN'T
MAKE ANY "PHOOS."

775
01:06:12,868 --> 01:06:16,372
- ANY WHAT?
- ANY "PHOOS."

776
01:06:16,372 --> 01:06:19,375
- ANY HOLES.
- ANY "HOOS."

777
01:06:19,375 --> 01:06:22,378
NO, IT'S "L, L, L."

778
01:06:22,378 --> 01:06:24,864
- "AHAHL?"
- "LE, LE, LE."

779
01:06:24,864 --> 01:06:27,867
"ACHH."
WATCH ME. "L."

780
01:06:27,867 --> 01:06:31,871
- "ELCH?"
- "LLLLLLLLLE."

781
01:06:31,871 --> 01:06:34,373
"ELLLL."
GOOD. AND NOW,
"O" AS IN "GO."

782
01:06:34,373 --> 01:06:36,876
"OOOOOO."
"OOOO."

783
01:06:36,876 --> 01:06:41,364
- "OOO."
- GREAT. HOLE.

784
01:06:41,364 --> 01:06:43,866
HOLE.
GREAT. TAKE A DEEP BREATH.

785
01:06:45,368 --> 01:06:48,371
-[ Phone Ringing ]
- HOL--

786
01:06:48,371 --> 01:06:51,874
HELLO?
WELCOME TO JAPAN.

787
01:06:51,874 --> 01:06:55,878
THANKS.
MY NAME IS
KAZUHIRO KATANAWA.

788
01:06:55,878 --> 01:06:58,364
BUT I GUESS THAT
MEANS NOTHING TO YOU.
NOTHING AT ALL.

789
01:06:58,364 --> 01:07:01,367
I'D LIKE VERY MUCH
TO MEET YOU, MR. FIORENTINI.

790
01:07:01,367 --> 01:07:03,869
IF YOU CAN SPARE
A FEW MINUTES.
WITH PLEASURE.

791
01:07:04,370 --> 01:07:06,872
HOLE.
I WAS TOLD THAT
YOU LIKE TO PLAY GOLF.

792
01:07:06,872 --> 01:07:09,875
I FIND IT
VERY PLEASANT, YEAH.
SO DO I.

793
01:07:10,376 --> 01:07:13,863
LET'S PLAY A ROUND TOGETHER.
MY MEN ARE DOWNSTAIRS.
THEY WILL DRIVE YOU.

794
01:07:13,863 --> 01:07:16,866
THAT'S FINE.

795
01:07:16,866 --> 01:07:19,368
HOLES.
THAT'S BETTER.

796
01:07:19,368 --> 01:07:21,871
WHAT'S HAPPENING?
I'M INVITED
TO PLAY GOLF.

797
01:07:21,871 --> 01:07:23,873
YOU'RE GOING GOLFING
AT A MOMENT LIKE THIS?

798
01:07:23,873 --> 01:07:28,377
IT HELPS YOU TO GET
PERSPECTIVE ON THINGS.
AND BESIDES, IN GOLF, YOU GOT--

799
01:07:28,377 --> 01:07:30,379
HOLES.
AH.

800
01:07:30,379 --> 01:07:32,865
- "HOOS."
- FORGET ABOUT IT.

801
01:07:34,867 --> 01:07:37,870
- COULD YOU HAVE
  THE ROOM MADE UP?
- RIGHT AWAY, SIR.

802
01:07:40,372 --> 01:07:42,875
HUBERT!

803
01:07:42,875 --> 01:07:44,877
HUBERT!

804
01:07:44,877 --> 01:07:48,364
LOOK, HUBERT! HUBERT.
CLEAN OUT YOUR EARS.

805
01:07:48,364 --> 01:07:52,368
- I GOT EVERYTHING.
- MOMO, WE GOT FRIENDS
  WAITING FOR US AT THE DOOR.

806
01:07:55,371 --> 01:07:59,875
TEN FOUR. I GOT THE STUFF
ON MIKO. AND HER NAILS.
I HAVE ALL THE RESULTS.

807
01:07:59,875 --> 01:08:04,363
TAKE THIS AND DON'T LOOSE IT.
FOLLOW US AT A DISTANCE.
ANY TROUBLE, YOU GOT US COVERED.

808
01:08:23,365 --> 01:08:24,867
[ Starter Firing ]

809
01:08:27,870 --> 01:08:29,872
[ Starter Firing ]

810
01:08:30,372 --> 01:08:31,874
COME ON,
YOU MOTHERFUCKER. START.

811
01:08:34,376 --> 01:08:36,378
HUBERT--

812
01:08:36,378 --> 01:08:39,365
I, UH--
SHOOT.
[ Starter Firing ]

813
01:08:52,878 --> 01:08:54,864
???? [ Guitar ]

814
01:09:18,370 --> 01:09:21,874
?? STARS SHINE ??

815
01:09:23,375 --> 01:09:25,878
?? NEVER GONNA FIND ME ??

816
01:09:27,379 --> 01:09:29,865
?? STARS SHINE ??

817
01:09:31,367 --> 01:09:35,371
?? WHERE YOU GONNA FIND ME ??

818
01:09:35,371 --> 01:09:39,375
OH, NO. COME ON.
YOU LOOK LIKE AN AMATEUR.
USE THE PROPER STANCE.

819
01:09:40,876 --> 01:09:43,379
?? NEVER GONNA FIND ME ????

820
01:09:43,379 --> 01:09:46,365
ADDRESS THE BALL.
YOU LOOK LIKE A DUCK
WHO'S ABOUT TO MATE.

821
01:09:50,369 --> 01:09:53,372
AT LEAST KEEP
YOUR EYE ON THE BALL.

822
01:09:55,374 --> 01:09:58,377
LOOK AT THAT.
GOLFING ON PLAYSTATION
IS MORE FOR YOU.

823
01:09:58,377 --> 01:10:00,863
YOU WON'T LOOSE
A LOT OF BALLS, ANYWAY.

824
01:10:03,365 --> 01:10:05,367
YOU PLAY VERY WELL,
SO I'VE HEARD.

825
01:10:05,367 --> 01:10:07,369
WELL, I DON'T USUALLY MISS.

826
01:10:11,373 --> 01:10:14,877
- THEY TELL ME YOU ARE SO GOOD
  IT'S DANGEROUS.
- LET'S NOT GO CRAZY.

827
01:10:17,363 --> 01:10:19,865
COULD I PREVAIL ON YOU
TO GIVE ME A DEMONSTRATION?

828
01:10:28,874 --> 01:10:32,878
WHY HAVE YOU RETURNED?
WHY COME BACK TO JAPAN
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS?

829
01:10:32,878 --> 01:10:36,865
- MEMORIES AREN'T BAD ENOUGH?
- AFTER A FEW YEARS,
  YOU REMEMBER ONLY THE GOOD.

830
01:10:36,865 --> 01:10:40,369
ISN'T WHAT BROUGHT YOU
TO JAPAN, IN REALITY,
A VERY HUGE SUM?

831
01:10:40,369 --> 01:10:43,372
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

832
01:10:43,372 --> 01:10:49,378
ABOUT THE $200 MILLION
YOU DISCOVERED THIS AFTERNOON
IN YOUR DAUGHTER'S ACCOUNT.

833
01:10:51,363 --> 01:10:52,865
MY FATHER?

834
01:10:56,368 --> 01:10:59,371
BASTARD! I HATE YOU!
YOU LIAR!

835
01:10:59,872 --> 01:11:02,374
YUMI, CALM DOWN.

836
01:11:03,876 --> 01:11:06,378
YOU DIRTY LIAR!
I HATE YOU!
CALM DOWN, YUMI.

837
01:11:06,378 --> 01:11:09,865
I TRIED TO TELL YOU,
BUT YOU HATE SO MUCH
YOU WOULDN'T LISTEN.

838
01:11:09,865 --> 01:11:12,368
TO YOU? THE JERK WHO
ABANDONED MY MOTHER AND ME?

839
01:11:12,368 --> 01:11:17,373
NO, YOUR MOTHER ABANDONED ME.
SHE JUST DISAPPEARED
ONE DAY WITHOUT A WORD.

840
01:11:17,373 --> 01:11:20,876
AND NO ONE TOLD ME
YOU EXISTED UNTIL
THE READING OF THE WILL.

841
01:11:20,876 --> 01:11:24,363
IF I KNEW I HAD SUCH
A GREAT DAUGHTER,
I'D HAVE COME RIGHT BACK.

842
01:11:24,363 --> 01:11:27,366
AND NOTHING COULD
HAVE TAKEN YOUR MOTHER
AND YOU AWAY FROM ME.

843
01:11:27,366 --> 01:11:29,868
I NEED YOU TO BELIEVE THAT.

844
01:11:35,374 --> 01:11:38,377
MY FATHER--

845
01:11:40,863 --> 01:11:42,865
MY BEAUTIFUL DAUGHTER.

846
01:11:43,365 --> 01:11:45,367
SO TOUCHING.

847
01:11:45,367 --> 01:11:48,871
SORRY TO DELAY THIS
WARM REUNION BETWEEN
BELOVED DAUGHTER AND HER FATHER.

848
01:11:48,871 --> 01:11:51,373
I ASK YOU TO GIVE BACK
OUR MONEY NOW--

849
01:11:51,373 --> 01:11:53,876
BUT EVEN YUMI CAN'T
WITHDRAW IT FROM THE BANK.

850
01:11:53,876 --> 01:11:58,364
IT'S FROZEN UNTIL
SHE REACHES... MAJORITY.

851
01:11:58,364 --> 01:12:01,867
WHICH SHE WILL REACH
IN AROUND NINE HOURS.

852
01:12:01,867 --> 01:12:04,370
WE CAN ALL GO
TO THE BANK AT 10:00.

853
01:12:04,870 --> 01:12:08,374
THE BIRTHDAY OF A DAUGHTER
IS A FINE THING.
CONGRATULATIONS.

854
01:12:10,876 --> 01:12:12,378
[ Speaking Japanese ]

855
01:12:12,378 --> 01:12:14,363
[ Speaking Japanese ]

856
01:12:16,865 --> 01:12:20,869
[ Speaking Japanese ]
FATHER! FATHER!

857
01:12:20,869 --> 01:12:26,375
[ Speaking Japanese ]

858
01:12:37,870 --> 01:12:40,372
WAIT.

859
01:12:48,364 --> 01:12:51,367
THIS IS A PRETTY DIFFICULT SHOT.
BUT WHEN YOU GET IT RIGHT,

860
01:12:52,868 --> 01:12:54,870
YOU CAN KNOCK 'EM DEAD.

861
01:12:59,875 --> 01:13:01,377
[ Shouts ]

862
01:13:41,867 --> 01:13:43,869
NOBODY MOVE!
FRENCH ARMY INTELLIGENCE!

863
01:13:43,869 --> 01:13:45,871
[ Coughing ]

864
01:13:46,371 --> 01:13:48,373
SHIT--

865
01:13:48,373 --> 01:13:50,375
HUBERT,
Y-YOU ALL RIGHT?

866
01:13:50,375 --> 01:13:54,863
IT'S TOO BAD.
YOU ONLY GOT HERE
A FEW SECONDS TOO LATE.

867
01:13:54,863 --> 01:13:58,367
OH, MAN--
THE GRENADE.
WHAT? WHAT GRENADE?

868
01:13:58,367 --> 01:14:00,369
I TOOK THE PIN OUT.

869
01:14:04,373 --> 01:14:06,375
HELL OF A GRENADE.

870
01:14:06,375 --> 01:14:09,378
NO, I LEFT
THE CASE IN THE TRUCK.
I GUESS THEY WENT OFF.

871
01:14:09,378 --> 01:14:13,365
- SO WHAT DID YOU FIND?
-MIKO LEFT THE CONSULATE 19
  YEARS AGO ON MATERNITY LEAVE.

872
01:14:13,365 --> 01:14:16,368
SHE NEVER WENT BACK TO WORK.
AND HER WHOLE FILE DISAPPEARED.

873
01:14:16,368 --> 01:14:19,872
BUT THE DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE
AT THE SAME TIME
OPENS A NEW FILE.

874
01:14:19,872 --> 01:14:22,875
ONLY IT'S TOP SECRET.
I COULDN'T GET
MY HANDS ON IT.

875
01:14:22,875 --> 01:14:24,877
HOWEVER,

876
01:14:24,877 --> 01:14:26,879
I GOT PICTURES.

877
01:14:28,363 --> 01:14:31,366
THESE ARE FROM MIKO'S FILE?
THEY LOOK LIKE WEDDING PICTURES.

878
01:14:31,366 --> 01:14:35,370
LOOK CLOSELY. THE GROOM.
HE'S THE SON OF A YAKUZA HEAVY
HITTER. BIGGEST IN THE NORTH.

879
01:14:35,370 --> 01:14:38,874
KATANAWA, ALSO KNOWN AS
"THE ZEBRA." HE'S GOT A--

880
01:14:38,874 --> 01:14:42,377
- YEAH, RIGHT,
  HE'S GOT A SCAR.
- Y-YOU KNOW THE GUY?

881
01:14:42,878 --> 01:14:44,863
ONCE PLAYED GOLF
WITH HIM. GO ON.

882
01:14:44,863 --> 01:14:46,865
IN THE BACK, SECOND ROW.

883
01:14:46,865 --> 01:14:50,869
- MIKO?
- MIKO. SO WHAT'S MIKO
  DOING WITH THOSE FIENDS?

884
01:14:51,370 --> 01:14:53,372
MIKO WAS SO HONEST.
I DON'T GET IT.

885
01:14:53,372 --> 01:14:55,874
HANG ON. I'M NOT FINISHED.
MIKO IS IN WITH THE MAFIA.

886
01:14:56,375 --> 01:14:58,877
THE SAME MIKO,
ONLY TWO WEEKS LATER,
GETS THE MINISTER'S AWARD...

887
01:14:59,378 --> 01:15:02,865
FOR DISTINGUISHED SERVICE
IN A CLOSED-DOOR CEREMONY.

888
01:15:02,865 --> 01:15:05,868
- WORKING UNDERCOVER.
- FOR THE GOVERNMENT.

889
01:15:05,868 --> 01:15:08,871
THAT EXPLAINS WHY
SHE NEVER WENT BACK TO WORK.
INFILTRATE...

890
01:15:08,871 --> 01:15:10,873
THE YAKUZAS IN ORDER
TO DESTROY THEM.

891
01:15:10,873 --> 01:15:16,378
BUT IT WAS IMPORTANT
TO LEAVE HER PAST BEHIND
AND ME WITH IT.

892
01:15:16,378 --> 01:15:19,364
A SACRIFICE SHE MADE...
FOR HER COUNTRY.

893
01:15:19,865 --> 01:15:21,867
YOU WOULD HAVE DONE IT
IN HER SHOES.

894
01:15:21,867 --> 01:15:24,369
I PROBABLY WOULD.

895
01:15:31,376 --> 01:15:33,879
THE REST IS SIMPLE.
SHE DOES SOME GOOD WORK.

896
01:15:33,879 --> 01:15:35,864
PUTS A FEW PEOPLE AWAY
BEFORE GETTING DISCOVERED.

897
01:15:36,365 --> 01:15:38,367
HER GOAL IS TO MAKE SURE
THE ZEBRA WILL CRUMBLE.

898
01:15:38,867 --> 01:15:42,371
SO SHE PUTS HIS MONEY SOMEPLACE
WHERE I CAN UNDERSTAND
AND FINISH THE JOB.

899
01:15:42,371 --> 01:15:44,873
- IF I WERE YOU,
  I'D BE CAREFUL WITH THAT.
- SURE, BUT--

900
01:15:45,374 --> 01:15:48,877
I STILL FEEL THERE IS
SOMETHING MISSING.

901
01:15:48,877 --> 01:15:50,879
WHAT'S THAT?

902
01:15:50,879 --> 01:15:55,367
I DON'T KNOW, BUT--
WHY'D SHE WAIT SO LONG
TO TELL ME I WAS A FATHER?

903
01:15:55,867 --> 01:15:58,870
MAYBE SHE DIDN'T
WANT YOU TO BE AWARE
OF THAT STUFF AND...

904
01:15:58,870 --> 01:16:01,873
THEN WHEN THEY MADE HER,
IT PUT YOUR DAUGHTER IN DANGER.

905
01:16:01,873 --> 01:16:04,876
- SHE KNEW YOU WOULD PROVIDE
  FOR THE PROTECTION OF YUMI.
- HER PROTECTION?

906
01:16:04,876 --> 01:16:07,863
YEAH, BECAUSE YOU KNOW YUMI.
SHE KNEW VERY WELL THAT...

907
01:16:07,863 --> 01:16:11,366
IF I WASN'T THERE, SHE'D SPEND
THE 200 MILLION OVERNIGHT.

908
01:16:11,366 --> 01:16:15,370
- TELL ME, WHAT'S THE NAME
  OF THIS STUFF?
- WASABI.

909
01:16:15,370 --> 01:16:17,873
REAL GOOD.

910
01:16:17,873 --> 01:16:20,375
REALLY. DELICIOUS.

911
01:16:31,870 --> 01:16:33,872
[ Chokes ]

912
01:16:35,374 --> 01:16:37,876
[ Hiccups ]

913
01:16:37,876 --> 01:16:41,863
[ Gags, Drinks ]

914
01:16:44,366 --> 01:16:46,868
DID THE DIRT UNDER HER NAILS
GIVE YOU SOME LOCATION?

915
01:16:51,873 --> 01:16:53,875
[ Squeaks ]

916
01:16:53,875 --> 01:16:56,378
[ Gurgles ]

917
01:17:01,867 --> 01:17:04,369
[ Gibberish ]

918
01:17:04,369 --> 01:17:06,371
- KYOTO.
- KYOTO!

919
01:17:06,371 --> 01:17:10,375
OF COURSE!
THAT'S WHERE IT BEGAN, WHERE
I DECLARED MY LOVE TO MIKO.

920
01:17:10,375 --> 01:17:13,879
AND NOW I KNOW WHY
THAT'S WHERE IT ENDS.
WE HAVE TO GO.

921
01:17:17,366 --> 01:17:20,369
[ Man On P.A.
  Speaking Japanese ]

922
01:17:23,872 --> 01:17:26,375
[ Woman On P.A. ]
KYOTO. KYOTO.
[ Speaking Japanese ]

923
01:17:27,876 --> 01:17:30,879
HURRY, WE HAVE TO BE
BACK IN TOKYO BEFORE 10:00.

924
01:18:19,878 --> 01:18:21,863
[ Woman's Voice ]
DEAREST HUBERT,

925
01:18:21,863 --> 01:18:25,867
I SACRIFICED MY LIFE
FOR MY COUNTRY
AND NOW I REGRET IT.

926
01:18:25,867 --> 01:18:30,872
I WISH I HAD SPENT
ALL THE YEARS AT YOUR SIDE
EVEN THOUGH, IN A WAY, I DID.

927
01:18:30,872 --> 01:18:35,377
BECAUSE YOU WERE ALWAYS SORT OF
WITH ME. YOU REMAINED IN MY
HEART, AND YOU ALWAYS WILL.

928
01:18:35,377 --> 01:18:39,865
TAKE GOOD CARE OF OUR DAUGHTER.
SHE'S WONDERFUL, BUT SHE SPENDS
TOO MUCH MONEY.

929
01:18:39,865 --> 01:18:43,368
HERE'S THE PIN NUMBER,
SO YOU CAN KEEP AN EYE
ON HER ACCOUNTS.

930
01:18:43,869 --> 01:18:47,873
THERE SHOULD NOW BE ENOUGH
MONEY FOR YOU AND OUR DAUGHTER
TO LIVE COMFORTABLY.

931
01:18:47,873 --> 01:18:49,875
IT ISN'T MUCH COMPENSATION
OF COURSE,

932
01:18:50,375 --> 01:18:53,879
BUT I HOPE OUR DAUGHTER
WILL MAKE ALL THOSE
BAD MEMORIES GO AWAY.

933
01:18:53,879 --> 01:18:56,865
LOOKING BACK THOUGH,
AREN'T ALL MEMORIES GOOD?

934
01:18:56,865 --> 01:18:59,367
YOURS FOREVER,
MIKO.

935
01:19:14,366 --> 01:19:16,868
ANY OF THE OLD GUYS
STILL UP HERE?

936
01:19:16,868 --> 01:19:21,373
ALMOST ALL OF THEM,
THE ONES WHO ARE LIVING.
LET'S GET EVERYBODY WE CAN.

937
01:19:29,364 --> 01:19:30,866
[ Yumi Yells ]
[ Slap ]

938
01:19:33,869 --> 01:19:36,371
AH!
[ Speaking Japanese ]

939
01:19:36,872 --> 01:19:38,373
[ Speaking Japanese ]

940
01:19:45,363 --> 01:19:47,866
CAPTAIN YASUMOTO, PLEASE.

941
01:19:56,374 --> 01:19:59,377
OH, HELLO.
DEPOSIT OR WITHDRAWAL?

942
01:19:59,377 --> 01:20:01,863
A WITHDRAWAL.
CASH OR
BANK-TO-BANK TRANSFER?

943
01:20:01,863 --> 01:20:03,865
BANK-TO-BANK.
FINE. HERE WE GO.

944
01:20:03,865 --> 01:20:07,869
REAL SIMPLE. ON THE LEFT
YOU PUT THE NUMBER
OF THE ACCOUNT YOU'RE FILLING.

945
01:20:08,370 --> 01:20:11,873
AND ON THE RIGHT,
THE ONE YOU'RE EMPTYING.

946
01:20:11,873 --> 01:20:14,876
- I SUPPOSE YOU CAN
  HANDLE THAT, RIGHT?
- RIGHT.

947
01:20:14,876 --> 01:20:17,863
[ Speaking Japanese ]

948
01:20:24,870 --> 01:20:27,873
"LAUSANNE." "LAUSANNE--"
IS THAT IN SWITZERLAND?

949
01:20:27,873 --> 01:20:30,876
- SWITZERLAND, YES.
- THAT'S BEAUTIFUL.

950
01:20:30,876 --> 01:20:33,879
- WE HAVE NO TIME.
  HURRY UP, PLEASE.
- OF COURSE, SIR. RIGHT AWAY.

951
01:20:36,865 --> 01:20:39,367
[ Typing ]

952
01:20:41,369 --> 01:20:44,372
[ Typing Continues ]

953
01:20:47,876 --> 01:20:50,879
ALL DONE!
NOW HOW MUCH
ARE WE TRANSFERRING?

954
01:20:50,879 --> 01:20:53,365
- ALL.
- CLOSING BOTH ACCOUNTS?

955
01:20:53,365 --> 01:20:55,367
RIGHT. CLOSE BOTH ACCOUNTS.

956
01:20:55,367 --> 01:20:58,870
- YEAH, YOU COULD BUY A LOT
  OF POONTANG WITH THAT.
- BUY WHAT?

957
01:20:58,870 --> 01:21:00,872
NO, I FIGURE IT'S, UH--

958
01:21:00,872 --> 01:21:05,377
$200 MILLION IS ENOUGH
TO BUY SOME GOOD TIMES.
I-IT'S A FAIR AMOUNT.

959
01:21:06,878 --> 01:21:09,364
HERE. UH--
YOU ARE OF AGE?

960
01:21:09,364 --> 01:21:12,367
YES. SHE TURNED 20 THIS MORNING.

961
01:21:12,367 --> 01:21:15,370
VERY GOOD, MY FRIENDS.
HOW 'BOUT SIGNING THEN?

962
01:21:25,864 --> 01:21:28,867
[ Under Breath ]
SIGN IT.

963
01:21:28,867 --> 01:21:30,869
[ Chuckles ]

964
01:21:32,370 --> 01:21:35,874
SIGN IT!

965
01:21:36,374 --> 01:21:38,877
THAT'S ALL! FINISHED.
MANY HAPPY RETURNS, YUMI.

966
01:21:38,877 --> 01:21:41,363
GIVE ME A RECEIPT.
STOP FOOLING AROUND.

967
01:21:41,363 --> 01:21:43,365
AH, NO, NO.
THE RECEIPTS, UH--

968
01:21:43,365 --> 01:21:46,868
THE RECEIPTS ARE RIGHT HERE.

969
01:21:46,868 --> 01:21:49,371
T-THE RECEIPTS
ARE THAT GUY.

970
01:21:53,375 --> 01:21:55,877
UH-UH. IF I WERE YOU,
I'D THINK TWICE ABOUT THAT.

971
01:22:04,369 --> 01:22:06,371
[ Yelling Japanese ]

972
01:22:09,374 --> 01:22:13,878
IF YOU HOPE TO LEAVE THIS BANK
UNHARMED, YOUR FRIEND
BETTER LOWER THAT WEAPON.

973
01:22:13,878 --> 01:22:16,865
YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO WILL HAVE TROUBLE
LEAVING HERE UNHARMED.

974
01:22:25,874 --> 01:22:28,877
YOU WIN,
MR. FIORENTINI. GOOD PLAY.

975
01:22:28,877 --> 01:22:31,363
TO BE A WINNER,
YOU HAVE TO LOSE SOME HANDS.

976
01:22:31,863 --> 01:22:34,366
WHAT'S YOUR PRICE?
I'LL PAY IT.

977
01:22:34,366 --> 01:22:36,368
YOU CAN'T AFFORD
TO PAY MY PRICE.

978
01:22:36,368 --> 01:22:39,871
ALL THE MONEY'S
NOW IN MY ACCOUNT.
I'M SORRY TO RUIN YOUR PLANS.

979
01:22:40,372 --> 01:22:42,374
SO LONG, $200 MILLION, HUH?

980
01:22:44,876 --> 01:22:46,878
YUMI, IT'S ALL RIGHT.

981
01:22:46,878 --> 01:22:48,863
COME HERE.

982
01:23:25,367 --> 01:23:28,370
[ Man On P.A. Indistinct ]
[ Chattering ]

